{ Welcome to this interactive MoveTrainer™ course based on one of the most instructional chess books ever written.  Before you begin this amazing course, here are a  few useful things to know:  We launched a completely new feature/setting for this course, called 'Learn important only'. It is enabled by default, and it allows you to study only the 'blue highlighted' lines that Dvoretsky himself deemed essential to memorize.  This new setting skips over everything else, but you are free to change it and study it all if you'd like. You can change this setting under 'Course Options' in your chapter list for this course.  Furthermore, the course has everything that the print book has, all the full text and analysis. All the main lines are trainable/drillable on the site. While this means there are over 1,000 trainable lines, most of the side analysis was not made trainable to keep things manageable.  If you'd like some side analysis to become 'trainable', please comment on it, and we will consider the request. We can potentially expand the number of trainable lines there is. You are also free to create a private book, and add such lines to your private course for personal study which may be quicker.  I also wanted to mention that this book had one of our most rigorous beta-tests yet. User 'logozar' achieved 220,000 points alone during the beta period. We had many testers and would like to extend thanks to them all.   Despite this for a course of this magnitude it is impossible to test it all. This means that some of our first users have a small chance of encountering some blemishes.  However, don't worry - please remember, Chessable courses are 'living' works, continually updated and improved. Just let us know if you spot anything and we will be right on top of it.  Finally, Mark Dvoretsky himself was a big advocate of repetition as a way to improve learning and retention. I hope that between the team, all of you who requested this book, all of you who bought it and all of you who will contribute with feedback, we've made him proud.  After all, we have now brought perhaps his greatest ever work to THE platform for the most efficient spaced repetition based study of his instructional material. In this way, I hope we have all contributed at least a tiny bit so that Dvoretsky's legacy lives on for a long time to come. Thank you Mr Dvoretsky.  Thank you and enjoy the course!  David Kramaley  Co-founder  September 3rd, 2018 }
