{ Key Squares are what we call those squares whose occupation by the king assures victory, regardless of whose turn it is to move.  In other types of endgames, we may also speak of key squares for other pieces besides the king.  The d5-square on which the king now stands is not a key square - White to move does not win. The key squares are c6, d6 and e6. Black to move must retreat the king, allowing the enemy king onto one of the key squares. With White to move, the position is drawn, since he cannot move to any key square. }
