{ Tragicomedies: Yates − Tartakower, Bad Homburg 1927  Black has a won position. }
1... Qxb4
{ 1...axb3  is possible, while  1...Qc3!?  2.Rxb5+   2.Ka2  Qc2+  ;  2.bxa4  Qxa3  .  2...Kc6  3.bxa4  Qxa3  is also strong. Tartakower, however, decided to transpose into a pawn ending, which he thought was won. }
2. axb4 axb3 3. Kb2 Kc4 4. Ka3 b2 { 4...Kc3  is stalemate. } 5. Ka2
{ Black had missed this move when he traded off his queen. He had hoped to win the b4-pawn and seize the opposition, but miscalculated. }
5... Kc3 6. Kb1 Kxb4 7. Kxb2 { The draw is obvious. } *

