{ Tragicomedies: Yusupov − Ljubojevic, Linares 1992    White’s rook is tied to the defense of the pawn at g3. Black would have won easily if he had retreated his rook by  1...Ra3!  @@StartBracket@@to prevent the White king from approaching the pawns:  2.Ke4  f5+!  and 3...Kf6 wins@@EndBracket@@,  followed by ...Kf6-g7 and ...f7-f6 or ...f7-f5.  Instead, Black blundered. }
1... Rf5 2. Ke4 Rxg5 3. hxg5
{ White has the opposition, but Ljubojevic had counted on } 3... f6 4. gxf6
Kxf6 5. Kf4 g5+ 6. Kf3
{ Yusupov's reply − it became clear that the opposition on the f-file would give Black nothing. }
6... Kf7
{ Since  6...Kf5  is met by  7.g4+!  hxg4+  8.Kg3=  And as soon as Black's king goes to the e-file, White's king immediately takes the opposition. }
7. Kf2 Ke6 8. Ke2 Kd6 9. Kd2 Kc5 10. Ke3 { Draw. } *

