{ 1/5. An Ancient Problem  Mate Black with just one  (mating)  move by the rook. The white king must come closer to the black one, maintaining the opposition. And, when this is impossible, to outflank along the c-file. In fact, all this is an algorithm that we know already − a transformation of a distant opposition into a close one. }
1. Ka2 Kb8 2. Kb2 Ka8 { 2...Ka7  3.Ka3!  Kb7  4.Kb3 } 3. Kc3 Kb7
{ 3...Ka7  4.Kc4! } 4. Kb3 Ka7 5. Kc4 Kb8 6. Kb4 Ka8 7. Kc5 Kb7 8. Kb5 Ka7 9.
Kc6 Kb8 { 9...Ka6  10.Ra1#  and  9...Ka8  10.Kc7  . } 10. Kb6 Ka8 11. Rc8# *

