[SetUp "1"]

{ Here, kings at e6 and c5 result in reciprocal zugzwang. White wins by forcing his opponent to go to the mined square first. }
1. Kf6 Kb5
{ Passive defense is hopeless too:  1...Kc7  2.Ke7  Kc8  3.Kxd6  the king captures the d6-pawn while simultaneously controlling the key square for the d5-pawn. }
2. Ke7 Kc5 3. Ke6 { Zugzwang. } *

