{ 1/7. Taimanov-Botvinnik, USSR ch tt, Moscow 1967 } 1... Rg4 2. Rxg4
{ 2.Rxa6  Rxh4  -+ } 2... hxg4 3. Kg2 g5
{ 3...Kf6  4.Kg3  it is not late for Black to play  4...g5!  as  4...Kf5?  is wrong:  5.e4+!  Kxe4  6.Kxg4  e5  7.Kg5  Kf3  8.Kxg6  e4  9.h5= }
4. h5
{ @@StartSquare@@Ed.  4.hxg5  Kg6  is Black's idea, followed  by Kg6xg5 with a technically winning position.  @@EndSquare@@   4.Kg3  Kg6  5.Kxg4  does not help:  5...gxh4  6.Kxh4  Kf5  7.Kg3  Ke4  8.Kf2  a5!?   Rather than  8...Kd3  9.Kf3  e5?  10.a3=  9.Ke2  a4  10.a3  e6!  11.Kd2  Kf3  12.Kd3  e5⨀  -+ }
