{ Tragicomedies: Yudasin − Osnos, Leningrad 1987  With his last move  (1.Ke2-f2)  , Yudasin offered a draw, adding that this position was a well-known draw, which one might find in any book. His opponent, an international master and an experienced trainer  (he trained Viktor Korchnoi for many years)  believed him, and accepted his offer!  After the next moves, we reach a position which is, indeed, in all endgame books,Fahrni - Alapin, but it's a win. }
1... Ke4 2. Ke2 f4 3. Kf2 f3 { Black wins by triangulation. } 4. Kf1 Kf5 5. Ke1
Ke5 6. Kf1 Ke4 { White is in zugzwang and can resign. } *

