{ 1/12. A. Troitsky, 1913 } 1. f6
{ White must eliminate the g2-pawn. After the premature  1.a4?  bxa3  2.bxa3  Kg3!  3.a4  h5  his king will be mated.   However after  1.Kxg2?  Kg5  2.a4  bxa3  3.bxa3  the black king enters the square of the a-pawn and arrives in time to hold the 8th rank:  3...Kf6!  4.a4  Ke7!  5.Kf3  or  5.a5  Kd8  , etc. }
1... gxf6 2. Kxg2 Kg5 3. a4 bxa3 4. bxa3 Kf5
{ Diagram 16-7  The 6th rank is not available anymore. Black must use the 5th rank. However, White creates barriers to this route, too. }
5. a4
{ 5.d6?  cxd6  6.a4  is premature in view of  Ke6!  7.c6  dxc6  8.a5  Kd7  . }
5... Ke5 6. d6 { Rather than  6.c6?  d6! } 6... cxd6 7. c6 dxc6 8. a5 Kd5 9. a6
{ White wins. } *

