{ Tragicomedies: Yates − Marshall, Karlsbad 1929    1.Qc4+  Ka3  2.Qc2?  or  2.Qb5?  is a mistake, in view of  2...b1=Q!  3.Qxb1  stalemate.   But White wins easily after  1.Qc2  a3  2.Kc3  Ka1  3.Kb3  b1=Q+  4.Qxb1+  Kxb1  5.Kxa3  +-  when the Black king can't reach the square @@StartBracket@@remember that when the pawn is on the 2nd rank, the square is constructed from f3, not from f2@@EndBracket@@.  In the game, White chose a less accurate method of transposing into a pawn endgame. }
1. Kc3 b1=Q 2. Qxb1+ Kxb1 3. Kb4
{ This is a situation known to us from theProkeš study. } 3... Kb2 4. Kxa4 Kc3
{ With a draw. } *

