{ 1/15. N. Grigoriev, 1937 } 1. h3 c5 2. Kb1 c4 3. Ka2
{ Black's has not managed to unite his pawns, so he relies on the Réti idea! }
3... c3 { Diagram 16-8 } 4. Kb3
{ By postponing the pawn capture, White gets the same position but with his king on a more favorable square: a2 instead of a3.   After  4.Kxa3?  Black holds by means of the Réti maneuver:  4...Kg3!  5.f5  Kf4!  6.f6  Ke3  7.Kb3  Kd3  8.f7  c2  9.f8=Q  c1=Q= }
4... a2 5. Kxa2 Kg3 6. f5 Kf3
{ If  6...Kf4  then  7.f6  Ke3  8.f7  c2  9.f8=Q  c1=Q  (the pawn is promoted without check)  10.Qh6+  winning the new queen. }
7. Kb1
