{ Let's shift the pawns to a6 and e6. The square now reaches only to the second rank, and the position becomes a draw.   In fact,  1...a5?  would be bad:  2.Kb5  e5  3.Kxa5  +-   And so is  1...Kh6?  2.Kd6!  a5  3.Kxe6  a4  4.Kf7  a3  5.g7  a2  6.g8=Q  a1=Q  7.Qg6#  Black must play: }
1... Kf6 2. Kc6 { But not  2.Kb6?  e5  3.Kc5  a5  -+ } 2... Kg7
{ 2...e5  3.Kd5  a5  4.g7  Kxg7  5.Kxe5=  is possible, too. } 3. Kc5 { Draw. }
*

