[SetUp "1"]

{ Let's examine one more substantive case.   On the queenside, the square does not reach the edge of the board, so the pawns can be held. }
1. Kc3 a3 2. Kc2
{ On the kingside, however, the pawns are already quite far advanced. True, the king can prevent them from queening − so far; but because of zugzwang, he will soon be forced to let them through. }
