{ However, with the white king at f7, the exchange of queens leads to victory. }
1. Qc2 Ka1 2. Ke6 b1=Q 3. Qxb1+ Kxb1 4. Kd5 Kc2 5. Kc4
{ The first, but not the last time we shall see 'shouldering' used in this book. }
5... Kd2 6. Kb5 { White wins. } *

