[SetUp "1"]

{ 1/19. Bologan-Vokác, Ostrava 1993 } 1. Kb8
{ The game continued  1.Bxg2?  hxg2  2.Kb7  g1=Q  3.a7  As we know from the discussion atDiagram 1-62, White is lost here: the black king arrives in time to arrange a mating attack.  3...Qb1+  4.Ka8  Qc2   4...Qh7!  would have made the process shorter.  5.Kb7  Qb3+  6.Ka8  Qc4  7.Kb7  Qb5+  8.Ka8  Qc6+  9.Kb8  Kd6!  White resigned.  Baron has shown that White could hold the draw by retaining his bishop. }
1... g1=Q 2. a7 Qg8+ 3. Kc7 { 3.Bc8?  Qb3+  4.Bb7  h2  -+ } 3... Qf7+ 4. Kb6
{ Draw. } *

