{ 1/21. A. Troitsky, 1935 } 1. Ke5
{ 1.Kc5?  loses after  1...Rd8  2.e7  Re8  3.Kd6  e3  4.Rxc4  g3  5.Re4  Kf2  . In case of @@StartFEN@@4r3/2R1P3/8/2K5/2p1p1p1/8/8/6k1 w - - 1 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Kxc4  g3  or  3...e3  4.Kd3  Kf2  . }
1... e3 { 1...Rd8  2.Kxe4= } 2. Rxc4 { 2.e7?  e2  -+ } 2... e2 3. Rxg4+
{ 3.Re4?  Kf2  4.e7  e1=Q  5.Rxe1  Kxe1  6.Kf4  Rf3+  7.Ke4  Ke2  -+ } 3... Kf2
4. Re4 { 4.Rf4+  Rf3  5.Re4  is equivalent. } 4... Re3 5. Rxe3 Kxe3 6. e7 e1=Q
{ Diagram 16-11 } 7. Ke6 Kf4+ { 7...Kd4+  9.Kd7!= } 8. Kf7 { Draw. } *

