{ 1/24. A. Khachaturov, 1947  (after N. Grigoriev, 1930)   Who finishes first in the coming breathtaking pawn race? }
1. f5 { White can win only if he promotes with check. } 1... Kc5 2. h5
{ Rather than  2.f6?  Kd6  and the black king enters the square of the h-pawn. }
2... g3 3. Ke1
{ This is essential for postponing an eventual check from the d-pawn for as long as possible.   @@StartSquare@@Ed. note:  3.Ke2  is not working in view of  3...d4  4.f6  d3+  5.Kxd3  g2  and Black escapes with a draw.@@EndSquare@@ }
3... d4 4. f6 Kd6 5. h6
{ White's technique is becoming clear. First the f-pawn is advanced, threatening to promote with check  (its mission is to decoy the black king to the eighth rank)  , then it is time for the h-pawn. }
5... g2 { If  5...d3  now  (without check!)  then  6.f7  Ke7  7.h7  +- } 6. Kf2
d3 7. f7 Ke7 8. h7 g1=Q+ 9. Kxg1 d2 10. f8=Q+ Kxf8 11. h8=Q+ { White wins. } *

