{ 1/32. I. Gabdrakipov, 1985  In this study we can see both kinds of zigzags again. }
1. Kd3 { 1.g4?  c5= } 1... Kb3 2. Kd4 Kb4
{ 2...h5  does not help:  3.g4!  hxg4  4.h5  c5+  5.Ke3! } 3. g4
{ Rather than  3.Ke3?  Kc5!= } 3... c5+ 4. Ke3 c4 { Diagram 16-18 } 5. g5
{ After  5.Kd2?  c3+  6.Kc2  Kc4  White has no win:  7.g5  hxg5  8.h5  g4=  and  8.hxg5  Kd5=  Or @@StartFEN@@8/8/7p/8/2k3PP/2p5/2K5/8 w - - 2 7@@EndFEN@@  7.h5  Kd4  8.g5  Ke5  9.g6  Kf6=  One should know this drawing position with a pawn less; a reminder will be given in the section devoted to the protected passed pawn. }
5... hxg5 6. h5
