{ The squares b5 and d3 are mined.   2.Kb5?  loses to  2...Kd3  ⨀  3.Kb4  c6!  4.Kxa4  c5  . }
2... Kd3 3. Kb5 c6+ 4. Kb4
{ Of course not  4.Kxc6?  Kc4!  -+  Now Black has no waiting move ...c7-c6, and his king is forced to leave the comfortable d3-square. Then White finally takes the a4-pawn and holds by means of a pendulum. }
