{ Tragicomedies: Rogers − Shirov, Groningen 1990    Black would have drawn, had he continued  1...f5+!  2.Kd4  Kg2=  or  2.Kxf5  Kxf3  3.Rxh2  Kg3  ∆  4.--  f3=   1...f6!  is also possible:  2.Rh8  f5+  or even  2...Kg2  . Shirov decided instead to pick up the rook for his h-pawn, but he misjudged the pawn ending. }
1... Kg2 2. Kxf4 h1=Q 3. Rxh1 Kxh1 4. Kg3
{ Black resigned. His king is squeezed into the corner, giving White time to push his f3-pawn forward, after which he can win Black’s pawn.   For example:  4...Kg1  5.f4  Kf1  and now not  6.Kf3?  f5! =  but  6.f5!  Ke2  7.Kf4  Kd3  8.Ke5  Ke3  9.f6!  +- }
*

