{ Breakthrough   A breakthrough occurs when one or more pawns are sacrificed in order to create a passed pawn and promote it. Let's examine a few of the standard structures in which a pawn breakthrough is possible.  White to move wins. }
1. b6 cxb6 { 1...axb6  2.c6  +- } 2. a6 bxa6 3. c6
{ Black to move has only one way to parry the threatened breakthrough @@StartFEN@@8/ppp5/8/PPP5/8/7k/8/7K b - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...b6!  Both  1...a6?  2.c6!  and  1...c6?  2.a6!  are bad. }
*

