{ The standard pawn breakthrough does not work immediately:  1.c5?!  dxc5  just  2.b5?  cxd4+  , and  2.bxc5  bxc5  3.dxc5  Kf3=  White must prepare it, but how? Of the many king retreats, only one leads to success: 1.Kd2!!   All other first moves draw or even lose.  1.b5?  c5  -+ is even simpler or  1...cxb5  2.cxb5  d5  -+ and in case of @@StartFEN@@8/8/1p1p4/1p6/2PP4/2K5/6k1/8 w - - 0 2@@EndFEN@@  2.Kb4  bxc4  3.Kxc4  Kf3  4.Kd5  b5  -+   1.Kb2?!  Kf2  2.c5  bxc5  3.d5?  cxd5  4.b5  d4  5.b6  d3  -+   1.Kc2?!  c5=  or  1...Kf3  2.c5  bxc5!  3.d5?  cxd5  4.b5  Ke2  5.b6  d4  6.b7  d3+  and 7...d2-+.   1.Kd3?!  Kf3  2.c5  bxc5!  3.d5  cxd5  4.b5  c4+  5.Kd4  c3!  6.Kxc3  Ke3=   1.d5?!  c5!  2.bxc5  bxc5  3.Kb3  Kf3  4.Ka4  Ke4  5.Kb5  Kd4  6.Kc6  Kxc4  7.Kxd6  Kb4  8.Ke7  c4=   1.d5?!  cxd5?  2.Kd4!  dxc4  3.Kxc4  Kf3  4.Kd5  +- }
