{ Lombardy − Fischer, USA ch, New York 1960-61    After  1.Ra1  − in spite Black's material advantage − it is not so easy to find a way to win. However, Lombardy committed 'harakiri': he allowed Fischer to obtain an easily won pawn ending, based on an outside passed pawn. }
1. Re1 Rxc3+ 2. bxc3 Rxe5+ 3. Kd2 Rxe1 4. Kxe1 Kd5 5. Kd2 Kc4 6. h5 b6
{ Black gets an outside passed a-pawn by force, which draws the white king to the edge of the board. }
7. Kc2 g5 8. h6 f4 9. g4 a5 10. bxa5 bxa5 11. Kb2 a4 12. Ka3 Kxc3 13. Kxa4 Kd4
14. Kb4 Ke3 { White resigned. } *

