[SetUp "1"]

{ One more useful addendum to the rule. Let's suppose that White's passed pawn is a rook's pawn, with the king in front of it, but the enemy king is boxing his opposite number in on the rook file. This situation is the same as the one in which the king is next to his pawn.    According to the rule formulated above, this is a draw. }
1... Kf5 2. Kh5 { 2.Kg3  Kg5  is the 'normal' position. } 2... Kf4
{ Black does not play  2...Kf6?  3.Kg4  when White has an extra tempo, because his king is in front of his pawn. }
3. h4 { 3.Kg6  Kg3= } 3... Kf5 4. Kh6 Kf6 5. Kh7 Kf7
{ Or  5...Kf5  6.h5  Kf6! } 6. h5 Kf6 { etc. } *

