[Result "*"]
[FEN "8/8/8/8/p4k1K/P7/7P/8 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ It must be noted here that this last rule does not work with the pawn on its starting square. Black has one tempo  (since the queenside pawns are one rank back)  , but if it is his move, he still loses. }
1... Kf3
{ The problem lies in the fact that the standard 1...Kf3 is impossible.   After  1...Kf5  2.Kg3  Kg5  White has not one, but two tempi  (the pawn is below the c8-h3 diagonal, and the king is in front of the pawn)  . }
2. Kg5 Kg2 3. h4 { White wins. } *

