{ 1/43. W. Bähr, 1935  White has seized the opposition and his king will inevitably break through to one of the wings. }
1... Ke7 2. Ke3 Kf7
{ Black gives away the a-pawn.   If he plays  2...Kd7?  and gives away the h-pawn, White wins with  3.Kf4  Kd6  4.Kg5  Ke5  5.Kxh5  Kf5  6.Kh6  Kf6  7.h5  Kf7  8.Kg5  Kg7  9.Kf5  because his a-pawn is above the middle line. }
3. Kd4 Kf6 4. Kc5 Ke5 5. Kb6 Kd6 6. Kxa6 Kc6 { 6...Kc7  is playable, too. } 7.
Ka7 Kc7 8. a6 Kc8 9. Kb6 Kb8 { A 'normal position' has arisen. } *

