[White "Chapter 1 – Pawn Endgames III"]
[Black "Diagram 1-137 Exercise 1/44"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "8/p7/8/7p/P1k4P/8/1K6/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ 1/44. W. Bähr, 1935 } 1. Kc2
{ 1.Ka3?  , hoping for  1...a5?  2.Kb2  Kb4  3.Kc2  Kxa4  4.Kc3  Kb5  5.Kb3=  , meets the refutation  1...Kc3!  2.a5  Kc4  3.Ka4  Kc5!   3...a6?  4.Ka3  Kb5  5.Kb3  Kxa5  6.Kc4  Kb6  7.Kb4=  4.a6  Kb6  5.Kb4  Kxa6  6.Kc5  Ka5  ⨀ is even stronger than  6...Kb7  7.Kb5  Kc7  .  The a7-pawn is standing above the key diagonal f1-a6, giving Black the decisive tempo to win. }
1... Kb4 2. Kd3 Kxa4 3. Kc4
{ If White were on move here he would have been lost. } 3... a6 4. Kc5
{ 4.Kc3?  Kb5  -+ } 4... Ka5 5. Kc4 Kb6 6. Kb4
{ We come to a familiar drawing position. } *

