{ Two Pawns to One   These positions are generally won. } 1. Kd3 Kd5 2. Ke3 Ke5
3. Kf3 Kd5 4. Kf4 Kd6 5. Ke4 Ke6 6. Kd4 Kd6 7. Kc4
{ Black must give up the opposition. } 7... Kc7 8. Kd5
{ 8.Kc5?!  is inaccurate:  1...Kb7  and White cannot continue  9.b6?  because of  9...Ka6!  10.Kc6  stalemate. }
8... Kb6 9. Kd6 Kb7 10. Kc5 Kc7 11. b6+ Kb7 12. Kb5 { White wins. } *

