{ Now let’s look at the two most important drawn positions. The first is an elementary one, but it comes up rather regularly. The second is less likely to occur, but it is very instructive. }
1... Kb8 2. Kc6 Kc8
{ Move the whole position one file to the left @@StartBracket@@when looking from Black's perspective@@EndBracket@@: @@StartFEN@@8/2k5/1pP5/1P1K4/8/8/8/8 b - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@ White wins easily by sacrificing the pawn and then winning the enemy's last pawn. }
