{ Tragicomedies: Shirov − Timman, Wijk aan Zee 1996  (continued) } 5... Kd6
{ Both sides believed that 5...Kd6 was refuted by the pawn breakthrough. } 6.
h4 Kxc6 7. f5 gxf5 8. h5 Kd7 9. g6 hxg6 10. h6
{ But Black does not have to take on f5! He could draw with the continuation @@StartFEN@@8/2p4p/2k3p1/5PP1/7P/8/6K1/8 b - - 0 7@@EndFEN@@  7...Kd7  8.f6  Ke6  or  8...Ke8  .  This is the same position as in our previous example @@StartBracket@@a protected passed pawn versus an outside passed pawn@@EndBracket@@. The mined squares are c6 and d8. }
