{ Keres − Alekhine, Dresden 1936  Grigoriev demonstrated the simplest winning method, involving an undermining on the queenside. }
1... Ke5
{ On the other hand, Alekhine's plan of going into a queen endgame was also quite strong.  1...Kg4!?  2.d6  g2  3.Kf2  Kh3  4.d7  e3+!  5.Kf3  g1=Q  6.d8=Q  Qf2+  7.Ke4  e2  8.Qd7+  Kg2  9.Qg4+  Kf1  White resigned. }
2. Ke2 Kd6 3. Ke3 Kc7 4. Ke2 Kb7 5. Ke3 a6 { 5...a5 } 6. bxa6+ Kxa6 7. Ke2 Kb7
{ 7...b5??  8.d6  Kb6  9.cxb5= } 8. Ke3 Kc7 9. Ke2 Kd6 10. Ke3 b5 11. cxb5 Kxd5
{ Black wins. } *

