{ Tragicomedies: Golberg − Zhuk, USSR 1934 } 1... a4
{ 1...g6??  2.h6  g5  3.f5  wins.  And if @@StartFEN@@8/5pp1/5k2/p6P/5PP1/1p1K4/8/8 b - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...g5?  2.f5= }
2. g5+ Kf5
{ The only winning plan was undermining with ...f7-f6. But first, Black had to bring his king to h7. As Grigoriev pointed out, the right way was  2...Ke7!  3.Kc3  Kf8  4.Kb2  Kg8  5.Ka3  Kh7  6.Kb2  f6!  7.Ka3  fxg5  8.fxg5  Kg8  9.Kb2  Kf7  10.Ka3  Ke6  11.Kb2  Kf5  . }
3. Kc3 Ke6
{ Having let the win slip, Black now lets slip the draw, which he could have had by playing  3...f6!  4.g6  Ke6  . }
4. h6 gxh6 5. gxh6 Kf6 6. f5
{ Black resigned. We have already seen the final position in the chapter devoted to the rule of the square. }
*

