[White "Chapter 1 – Pawn Endgames III"]
[Black "Two Connected Passed Pawns 1-154"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "8/6k1/8/1p4PP/1Pp2K2/8/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ B. Horwitz, J. Kling, 1851  (continued) } 1. g6
{ The ideal pawn array!.   The erroneous  12.h6+?  would throw away the win. }
1... Kf6 2. Ke4 Kg7 3. Kf3 Kf6 4. Kf4 Kg7
{ Now that White has strengthened his position to its utmost, it is time for the decisive advance! }
5. Kg5 c3 6. h6+ Kg8 7. Kf6 c2 8. h7+ Kh8 9. g7+
{ Or  20.Kf7  c1=Q  21.g7+  +- } 9... Kxh7 10. Kf7 c1=Q 11. g8=Q+ Kh6 12. Qg6#
*

