{ Tragicomedies: Potter − Zukertort, London m  (5)  1875  The position is in fact the same as in our preceding example, which was published a quarter-century before this game. White, unacquainted with endgame theory, agreed to a draw here.   The win is elementary: }
1. b5 Ka7 2. b6+ Ka6 3. Kb4 Kb7 4. Kb5 d3 5. a6+ Kb8 6. Kc6 d2 7. a7+ Ka8 8.
b7+ Kxa7 9. Kc7 d1=Q 10. b8=Q+ Ka6 11. Qb6#
{ A century later, chessplayers, alas, continue to make the very same mistakes. }
*

