{ Mandler − Prochzka, Czechoslovakia 1976  (continued) } 1. Kf1
{ Again, not  6.a4?  a5=   Now Black must stalemate his own king, since  6...Kh2  allows an easy win by  7.a4  Kh1  8.a5  a6  9.Kf2  and if @@StartFEN@@8/p7/8/PP6/8/7p/8/5K1k b - - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  8...h2  9.Kf2  a6  10.Kf1  +- }
1... h2 2. b6
{ The only move!   White only gets a draw after  7.a4?  a5!  or @@StartFEN@@8/p7/8/1P6/8/P7/7p/5K1k w - - 0 2@@EndFEN@@  7.Kf2?  a5! }
2... a5 { 7...axb6  8.a4  b5  9.a5  +- } 3. b7 a4 4. Ke2 Kg1 5. b8=Q h1=Q 6.
Qb6+ { White wants mate. As can easily be seen, exchanging queens wins also. }
6... Kh2 7. Qd6+ Kg1 8. Qd4+ Kh2 9. Qh4+ Kg2 10. Qg4+ Kh2 11. Kf2
{ Black resigned. } *

