[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Chapter 1 – Pawn Endgames III"]
[Black "Reserve Tempi 1-170"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "8/6p1/5p1p/p7/Pk3PP1/3K3P/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Let's observe these rules in action. The first is illustrated in the following two examples. }
1. f5
{ This move secures White two reserve pawn tempi − just enough to squeeze the enemy king at the edge of the board. }
1... Kxa4 2. Kc4 Ka3 3. Kc3 a4 4. h4 Ka2 5. Kc2 a3
{ 5...h5  6.gxh5  a3  7.h6  gxh6  8.h5  is zugzwang. } 6. h5 Ka1 7. Kc1
{ Draw. } *

