[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Chapter 1 – Pawn Endgames III"]
[Black "Reserve Tempi 1-172"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "8/8/1p2k2p/1p3p2/1P3P2/P5Pp/5K2/8 b - - 0 4"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Despotovic − Dvoretsky, Moscow tt 1968  (continued) } 4... Kd5
{ Karsten Müller noted that if, instead of  4...Kd5  , Black were to try  4...Kf6  5.Kg1  Kg7!?  then the only move to draw would be  6.Kh1!  - the h2-square is mined.  The problem is that after  6.Kh2?  Kg6  7.Kxh3  Kh5  ⨀  8.g4+  Black does not play  8...fxg4+?  9.Kg3  Kg6  10.Kxg4  ⨀  Kf6   10...h5+  11.Kh4=  11.Kh5  Kf5  12.Kxh6  Kxf4  13.Kg6  when the white king reaches the queenside in time, but @@StartFEN@@8/8/1p5p/1p3p1k/1P3PP1/P6K/8/8 b - - 0 8@@EndFEN@@  8...Kg6!  9.Kh4  Kf6!  10.Kh5  fxg4  11.Kxg4  Kg6  − here, it is White who falls into zugzwang. }
5. Kg1 Kc4 6. Kh2 h5 { 6...Kb3?  7.g4! } 7. Kxh3 Kb3 8. Kh4 Kxa3 9. Kxh5
{ 9.Kg5!? } 9... Kxb4 10. g4 fxg4 11. Kxg4 Kc3 { 11...Kc5  12.Kf3! } 12. f5 b4
13. f6 b3 14. f7 b2 15. f8=Q b1=Q 16. Qf6+ { And the queen endgame is drawn. }
*

