{ Tragicomedies: Kachiani − Maric, Kishinev izt 1995  On the kingside − equality @@StartBracket@@each side has three pawn moves@@EndBracket@@. White has the reserve tempo a3-a4 on the queenside. Unfortunately, she was too eager to use it: }
1. a4
{ White wins by  1.Kc3!  Ke4  2.Kc4  Kxf4  3.Kd5  +- In case of  1...Ke6  2.Kc4  Kd6  3.d5  Kd7  4.Kd4  Kd6  5.a4  h6  6.h3  g6  7.h4  h5  8.f3  ⨀ And if @@StartFEN@@8/p5p1/1p1k3p/1P1P1p2/P2K1P2/7P/5P2/8 b - - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6...g5  7.fxg5  hxg5  8.f3  f4  9.Ke4  +- }
1... Kd6 2. Kc4 Ke6 3. d5+ Kd7 4. Kd4 Kd6
{ Here is where White could have used the reserve tempo - but alas, it is already gone. }
5. Kc4 Kd7 6. Kd3 Ke7
{ Of course, Black will not be the first to go to the mined square d6. The game soon ended in a draw. }
*

