{ Steinitz's Rule   Wilhelm Steinitz, the first world champion, put forth the following paradox: that the pawns stand best on their original squares. His explanation:  In the endgame, it is useful to have a choice of whether to advance a pawn one or two squares.   We shall see the point of his idea to its fullest extent in the following subchapters; so I shall limit myself to just one example of it here. The analysis given next was made by Artur Yusupov when he was still quite young, with the assistance of the author. @@StartSquare@@Ed. note: see the next variation → Diagram 1-178.@@EndSquare@@ }
1. -- *

