{ Tragicomedies: Marshall − Schlechter, San Sebastian 1911    1...Kg4!  2.Kf2  Kh3  decides:  3.Kg1  (White's king is on the wrong square: on h1, it would be a draw.)  3...g5  4.Kh1  g4  5.Kg1  h4  6.Kh1  g3  7.hxg3  hxg3  8.Kg1  g2  Black wins. }
1... Ke4
{ Instead, this is what Schlechter played, when the position was drawn, because both black pawns have now left their starting rank, and if Black tries to get his king into h3 @@StartBracket@@there is no other plan@@EndBracket@@, White's king can always choose the right square on the first rank. }
2. Kf2 Kd3 3. Kf3 g5 4. Kf2 Ke4 5. Ke2 Kf4 6. Kf2 Kg4 7. Kg2 h4 8. h3+
{ The simplest, although  8.Kg1  was possible, too. } *

