{ With White to move, there is no win. } 1. Ke2 Ke4 2. Kf2 h4
{ 2...Kd3  3.Kf3  h4  4.Kf4  Ke2  5.Kxf5= } 3. Ke2 h3 4. Kf2 Kd3 5. Kf3 Kd2 6.
Kf2
{ Draw.  Maizelis' position serves as a most important guidepost in analyzing situations where one side has an advanced rook's pawn − the outcome of the battle depends on whether the stronger side can reach Maizelis' position and whose move it is. }
