{ Tragicomedies: Laveryd − Wikström, Umeå 1997  (continued)     3...fxe5  is met by  4.g4!  and if  3...f5  then  4.f4  exf3  5.gxf3  f4  6.exf4  g6  7.f5  , or @@StartFEN@@8/6p1/4p3/2k1Pp1p/1pP4P/1K2PP2/8/8 b - - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  5...g5  6.hxg5  h4  7.g6  h3  8.g7  h2  9.g8=Q  h1=Q  10.Qf8+  Kc6  11.Qd6+  with an easily won queen endgame.  One must have an unusual gift for the fantastic  (or know some of Grigoriev's studies)  to find the idea of a stalemate haven in the middle of the board! }
1... fxe5 2. g4 g6 { 4...hxg4?  5.h5  +- } 3. g5 Kb6 { 5...Kd6! } 4. Kxb4 Kc6
5. c5 Kd5 6. Kb5 { stalemate. } *

