{ 2/2. L. Kubbel, 1934  (adapted as an exercise) } 1. Rb7
{ White can exchange rooks by force if he attacks the knight. But first, in order to make this endgame drawn, the h-pawn should be enticed to h3. }
1... h6
{ 1...Rh3?  2.Rb1  , and there is no  2...Nc2??  in view of  3.Rb3+  . } 2. Rb6
h5 3. Rb5 h4 4. Rb4
{ It turns out that  4.Kg2  also draws, but it is more complicated. } 4... h3
{ 4...Nc2  5.Rxh4  Ne3  6.h3= } 5. Rb1 Nc2 6. Rb3+ Ke2 7. Rxf3 Kxf3 8. Kh1
{ Or  8.Kf1  , with a draw. } *

