{ Knight vs. Rook Pawn    The closer the passed pawn to the edge of the board, the more difficulty the knight has dealing with it. The rook pawns are especially dangerous.  Here is a simple, yet instructive example.  A. Chéron, 1952 }
1. Ng7+ Nxg7 2. h6 Kf7 3. h7 { White wins. } *

