{ The Knight Defends The Pawn   The best way for the knight to defend the passed pawn is from the rear. Here, the knight is immune from capture, since that would put the king outside the square of the passed pawn. }
1. Nc4 { White parries the threat of  1...Kb4  . } 1... Kb4 2. Nd2 Kc3 3. Kg3
{ White wins. } *

