{ M. Dvoretsky, 2000  The knight can easily defend its pawn if both white and black pawns are on the same file, and the pawns blockade one another. }
1. Nb5
{ White can also play  1.Nd5  Kd4  2.Nb6  − in either case, the knight can handle it, without the king's assistance. }
1... Ke4 2. Kg2 Kd3 3. Nd6 { White wins. } *

