{ Eingorn − Beliavsky, USSR ch, Kiev 1986 } 1. Nd4+ Nxd4 2. Kf6
{ The king goes, as we taught, one square diagonally away from the knight; which renders the h-pawn unstoppable. }
2... Nc2 3. h5 Ne3 4. Kg5 { The same idea again. } 4... Nc4 5. h6
{ Black resigned as the h-pawn is unstoppable. } 5... Ne5 6. h7 Nf7+ 7. Kf6 Nh8
8. Kg7 { White wins. } *

