{ 3/1. H. Rinck, 1920 } 1. Ne7
{ A win of the knight for the g-pawn gives White nothing; he should try to deflect the knight from the passed pawn, exploiting the fact that Black's king is misplaced.   1.Nf6?  fails after  1...Nc6  ∆  2.--  Ne7  . }
1... Nd7 2. Nc6+ Kb6
{ On  2...Ka6  ,  the deflecting knight sacrifice decides:  3.Nb8+!  Nxb8  4.g7  .  And now, again, the same technique rapidly leads to the goal. }
3. Nxe5 Nf6 4. Nd7+ Nxd7 5. e5 { White wins. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
