{ Alburt − Lerner, Kiev 1978  Although Black might appear to be better, thanks to his more active king, Whites spectacular pawn break completely changes the picture. }
1. Nxc5 bxc5 2. b4 axb4
{ Let's examine the other possibilities:   a.  2...cxb4  3.c5  b3+  4.Kb2  or  4.Kxb3  Ne4  5.Kc4  +-   b.  2...e4  3.bxc5  Kf2  4.c6  e3  5.d7  e2  6.d8=Q  +-   c.  2...Nd7  3.bxa5  Kf2  4.a6  e4  5.a7  e3  6.a8=Q  e2  7.Qe4  e1=Q  8.Qxe1+  Kxe1  9.a5  +- }
3. a5 e4 4. a6 Kf2 5. a7 e3 6. a8=Q e2 7. Qf8 e1=Q 8. Qxf6+ Kg3
