{ R. Fine, 1941  (analysis)   We shall see in the main line that the winning method often involves displacing the black knight. Now White has more than one way to win. }
11. f4 { The simplest. } 11... Nc5 { 11...h5  12.Nf3  +- } 12. g4 fxg4 13. f5+
Kh5 14. f6 Nd3 15. Nc6
{ Müller.  Ed. note: Fine's analysis, presented in Diagram 3-21, continues in the next variation → Diagram 3-21c. }
