{ R. Fine, 1941  (continued from Diagram 3-21c) } 12. Nd4 Nb6 { Diagram 3-21e }
13. Nb5
{ The most natural move is  13.Ke4?  Nc4  14.Nc6+  Ke6  15.f5+  gxf5+  16.gxf5+  Kd7  17.Nb8+  Ke7  18.e6  Nd6+  19.Kf4  Nc4  @@StartBracket@@Diagram 3-21f@@EndBracket@@. Although it looks like White is close to breaking through, a win for White is not apparent. }
13... Nd7 14. Kd4 Nf8 15. Nc7 Kd7 16. Nd5 Ne6+ 17. Ke3 fxe5 18. fxe5 Nc5 19.
Nf4 Ke7 { Ed. note: continued in the next variation → Diagram 3-21g & 3-21h } *

[Event "?"]
