{ R. Fine, 1941  (continued)   We saw earlier that with Black to move, this position is drawn. With White to move, it is winning, but there is only one way. }
27. Ng6+ Kf7 { If  27...hxg6  28.h6!  +- } 28. e6+ Kf6 29. Nf8
{ 29.Ne5  Ke7  30.Nc6+  Kf6  makes no progress. } 29... h6 30. Nd7+ Ke7 31. Nb6
Kf6 32. Nc8 Nf3 33. e7 Kf7 34. Kd6 Ke8 35. Ke6 Ng5+ 36. Kf6 Ne4+ 37. Kg7
