10. h4
{ The position with the extra e-pawn and the pawns on g3, h4/g6, h5 is frequently drawn. If the pawn cannot advance to e4 it is usually a simple draw, and even if the pawn can reach e4 safely, it can be a draw if the white knight is well placed.   Another way to draw is  10.Ne2  and if  10...g5  11.g4+= }
10... e4+ 11. Ke3 Ke5 12. Ne2 Nd5+ 13. Kf2 Kf5 14. Nd4+ Kg4 15. Ne2
{ And Black cannot convert his advantage here.   Ed. note: the game continuation is given in the next variation → Diagram 3-21n. }
