10. Ke3
{ Giving the former world #2 a second chance, which he does not miss. @@StartSquare@@Ed. note: the following lines were trained in the previous variation.@@EndSquare@@   White could hold with  10.h4  The position with the extra e-pawn and the pawns on g3, h4/g6, h5 is frequently drawn. If the pawn cannot advance to e4 it is usually a simple draw, and even if the pawn can reach e4 safely, it can be a draw if the white knight is well placed:  10...e4+  11.Ke3  Ke5  12.Ne2!  Nd5+  13.Kf2  Kf5  14.Nd4+  Kg4  15.Ne2  and Black cannot convert his advantage here.   Another way to draw is  10.Ne2  and if  10...g5  11.g4+= }
10... g5 11. Nb5 { Nigel Short has a way to win a pawn by force and finds it. }
11... g4 12. hxg4+ { 12.h4  Ne4!  -+ } 12... Kxg4
