{ Tragicomedies: Fine − Najdorf, New York m  (3)  1949  White should hold the position. It is essential, however, not to move the pawn from h2:   1.Nf2  Ne3+  2.Kg1  Nc2  3.Nd3  g5  4.Kf2  Kh3  5.Kg1  Nd4  6.Nf2+  Kh4  7.Kg2  , and if @@StartFEN@@8/8/7p/6p1/5p2/3N1P1k/2n4P/6K1 b - - 3 5@@EndFEN@@  5...h5  6.Nf2+  Kh4  7.Nd3  etc. }
1. h3
{ Now Black has a forced win. He executes a deflecting sacrifice of his knight, which allows him to snap off the pawn at h3, and thereby obtain a decisive passed h-pawn. }
1... Ne3+ 2. Kh2 Nc2 3. Kg2 Ne1+ 4. Kf2 Kxh3 5. Kxe1 Kg2 6. Ke2 h5 7. Ng5 h4 8.
Ne6 g5 { White resigned, in view of } 9. Nxg5 h3 10. Nxh3 Kxh3 11. Kd3 Kg2 *

