{ Bishops versus Pawns   The Elementary Fortresses    There are many endgames in which the only way to defend consists of constructing a position impenetrable to the enemy. Such a position is called a fortress, and the method is called constructing a fortress.   I use the term “elementary fortress” to mean those theoretical positions with minimal material and a king usually placed on the edge or in a corner of the board, in which the stronger side proves unable to exploit a significant material advantage. We have already encountered such positions in the chapter on “Knight vs. Pawns” @@StartBracket@@Diagrams2-2,2-4, and2-5@@EndBracket@@. Here, and also in later chapters, you will learn other elementary fortresses which are important for the practical player. }
1. -- *

