{ Tragicomedies: Gutman − Mikenas, Riga 1969 } 1. Bg6
{ What could have been simpler than  1.e6  Kxf4  2.e7  Bd7  3.h6  +-, or  1.h6  Kxf4  2.e6  +-  ? }
1... Kxf4 2. Bxf5 Kxe5
{ Gutman evidently expected  2...Kxf5?  3.h6  Kg6  4.e6  +-  However, it is more important for Black to take, not the bishop, but the e-pawn. }
3. h6 Kf6 4. Kc2 Kf7 5. Bh7 Kf6 6. Bg8 Kg6 7. h7 Kg7 { Draw. } *

