{ Tragicomedies: Gershon – Thorhallsson, Bermuda 1999    Here too, the win is elementary:  1.Kg5  h3  2.g3  , followed by 3.Bf5 – White winds up two pawns ahead. Gershon chose a different way, making the same mistake Gutman did in the preceding example: he only expected Black to take his attacked bishop. }
1. h3 gxh3 2. gxh3 Ba6 3. Kg5 Bxb7 4. Bxb7 Kd7
{ On  5.Kxh4  , the black king has time to get to h8; otherwise, we haveRauzer’s drawn position. The game ended in a draw. }
