{ Tragicomedies: Fischer – Taimanov, Vancouver cmqf  (2)  1971    Where should Black put his king in the next diagram? As close as possible to  h8  , of course. The most accurate way to draw was:  1...Nd3!  2.h4  Nf4  3.Kf5  Kd6!  4.Kxf4  Ke7=  . Also possible was  1...Kd6  2.Be2  Nd7+  3.Kf7  Ke5  4.h4  Nf6=  . Amazingly, the highly experienced grandmaster sent his king off in the opposite direction. }
1... Ke4 2. Bc8 Kf4 { 2...Nf3  3.Bb7+  and if  2...Nd3  3.Bf5+  . } 3. h4
{ Nothing can save him now: as you will recall, the knight has a difficult time with rook pawns. }
3... Nf3 4. h5 Ng5 5. Bf5 Nf3 6. h6 Ng5 7. Kg6 Nf3 8. h7 Nh4+ 9. Kf6
{ Black resigned. } *

