{ Dombrowska – Lyszowska, Polish ch 1988 } 1. Kg1
{ White had to play  1.Kh2!  Black can neither drive White’s king from the corner, nor put White in zugzwang. For example,  1...Kf3  2.Kh3  Bc5  3.Kh2  Bd4  4.Kh1!=  But not  4.Kh3??  Bg1  ⨀. }
1... Kh3
{ If  2.Kh1  , then  2...Bc5  ⨀  2.g4  hxg4  , and the rook pawn becomes a knight pawn. And on @@StartFEN@@8/8/3b4/7p/7P/6Pk/8/6K1 w - - 2 2@@EndFEN@@  2.Kf1  , either  2...Kh2  or  2...Bc5  decides. Therefore, White resigned. }
