{ 4/2. G. van Breukelen, 1969  Is it possible to prevent the black king's march to the corner ? Yes, if White manages to discover the reciprocal zugzwang positions and reach them with Black to move. }
1. Kd7
{ After @@StartFEN@@6B1/4K3/8/6k1/8/7P/8/8 w - - 4 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Ke8  Kh5!  or  3...Kf6!  4.Kf8  Kg6  ⨀, because both zugzwang positions arise with White on move. }
1... Kf4 2. Ke8 Kg5 { 2...Kf5  3.Kf7  +- } 3. Ke7 Kg6 4. Kf8 Kh6
{ 4...Kf6  5.Bf7  +- } 5. Kf7 Kg5 6. Kg7 { White wins. } *

