{ 4/3. A. Gerbstman, 1928 } 1. b6 axb6
{ 1...Kc6  2.Be7!  Kb7  3.Bd8  +- and @@StartFEN@@8/p3B3/1Pkp4/P7/8/8/4K3/8 b - - 2 2@@EndFEN@@  2...axb6  3.a6  is the same. }
2. a6 Kc6 3. Be7
