{ Tragicomedies: Paulsen – Metger, Nürnberg 1888 } 1. Kc4
{ The game continuation  1.Kc5?  also drew after  b6+!   The winning move was  1.Kd4!  b5  2.a6  Kc6  3.Kc3  , or  1...b6  2.a6  Kc6  3.Kc4  .   If after  1.Kd4!  Black goes  1...Kc6  , now not  2.Kc3?  b6!  3.a6  Kb5=  , but  2.Bb6!  Kb5  3.Kd5  Ka6  4.Kd6  , and if  2...Kd6  3.Kc4  Kc6  4.Kb4  Kd7  5.Kc5  Kc8  6.Ba7  Kc7  7.Kb5  Kd7  8.Bb8  Kc8  9.Bf4  Kd7  10.Kb6  Kc8  11.Be5  +- }
1... b5+
{ The draw would have been inescapable since either Black's king reaches the corner not controlled by the bishop  2.Kxb5  Kb7  , orPonziani's position is reached  2.axb6+  Kb7  .   But not  1...b6+?  2.a6!  +- }
