{ Let's use the ideas from the position we just looked at to analyze other positions.   Move all the pieces one rank further up. What has changed?   On  1...Bb4  , nothing. White wins by the exact same method @@StartBracket@@check, followed by a king outflanking@@EndBracket@@; here, both checks − from  g6  or  b5  − are equally good. }
1... Bd8 2. Bg6+ { Or  2.Bb5+  . } 2... Kf8 3. Kf5
{ Black loses because of zugzwang − compared to the previous position, he no longer has any waiting moves with his bishop. }
