{ M. Henneberger, 1916  (continued)   However, Whites' resources for playing to win are not yet exhausted. We could decoy the king to g7 first, and then put the bishop on the e8-h5 diagonal, thus preparing a left-hand outflanking by the king. }
1. Kg4 Bb2 2. Kh5 Kg7
{ White threatened 3.Kh6.   2...Bg7?  is bad because of  3.Bc4+  and 4.Kg6. }
3. Bb5 Bc3 4. Be8 Bd4 { 4...Kf8  5.Bg6  Kg7  is the same thing. } 5. Bg6
{ @@StartSquare@@Ed.  5.Kg4  can be trained next → Diagram 5-6 EXTRA*.@@EndSquare@@ }
5... Bc3 6. Kg4 { Ed. note: continued →Diagram 5-7 } *

