[SetUp "1"]

{ Y. Averbakh, 1950  The draw is obvious. } 1. Kd5 Kf6
{ If the king goes to b7, Black's king turns up at d8. Black can draw in large part because his bishop restrains both pawns along the b8-h2 diagonal. }
*

