[SetUp "1"]

{ Berger − Kotlerman, Arkhangelsk 1948  And finally, the standard winning plan often does not work because the edge of the board is too close @@StartBracket@@for example, when one of the pawns is a knight's pawn@@EndBracket@@. The following position has great practical significance. }
1. Ke2 b3 2. Kd1 Kb4 3. Bh7 Ka3 4. Bg6
{ If  4...b2  threatening 5...Ka2, then  5.Bb1!  Kb3  6.Ke2= } 4... Kb2 5. Bf7
{ Black threatened  5...Ka1  and  6.--  b2  . White stops this plan by attacking the b3-pawn. }
5... Ka2 6. Be6 Ka3 { Threatening  7.--  b2  8.Bf5  Ka2  . } 7. Bf5 { Draw. } *

