{ Tragicomedies: Cifuentes – Langeweg, El Vendrell 1996 } 1... Ke5
{ A strange move indeed! Common sense would indicate Black should exchange on  h4  .  The side that is down material should usually exchange pawns whenever possible.   Black’s refusal to trade pawns probably stems from the fact that Langeweg did not want to free the g3-square for White’s king. The king cannot approach through the h3-square, which can be seen from the line  2.Kh3  Kd6!  3.Kg4  gxh4  or  3...Kc7  4.hxg5  hxg5  5.Bxe4  Bxe3  . In case of  4.h5  Bxe3  5.Bxe4  Bd2  6.Kf5  g4!=  Black can also play  4...Kxb7  instead,  5.Bxe4+  Kc7=  . }
2. h5 { Ed. note: analyzed in the next variation → Diagram 5-21 } *

