{ The Bishop Restrains The Passed Pawn   Situations in which the bishop stops a passed pawn  (and sometimes two − on the same diagonal)  we call the  second defensive system. The weaker side's king in these cases "maintains the zone" − that is, it defends its pawns, and limits the activity of the opposing king.    Attempts to break down the second defensive system invariably involve breaking through to the passed pawn with the king @@StartBracket@@often after a preliminary diversionary attack, and "widening the beachhead" on the other wing@@EndBracket@@. }
1. -- *

