{ An instructive error: the white king should not have been allowed near the pawns. The draw becomes unavoidable after  5...Kf5!  6.Bf8  g6  7.Kd4  Bg2  8.Kc5  Ke6!  9.Kb6  Kd7  10.b4  Ba8  11.b5  Kc8!=  But not  11...Bg2?  in view of  12.a8=Q!  Bxa8  13.Ka7  Bf3  14.Kb8  +-, with the unstoppable threat of b5-b6-b7. }
6. Kf4 g6 7. g4 { The first step is to widen the kingside beachhead. } 7...
hxg4 8. Kxg4 Bh1 9. Kg5 Kf7 10. Bd4 Bg2 11. h4 Bh1 12. b4 Bg2 13. b5 Bh1
