{ But what is Black to do if it is his move? Any bishop retreat along the h1-a8 diagonal, for example,  1...Ba8  is refuted by  2.Bd5  . Therefore, he must play the text move. }
1... Ba6
{ By the way  (here's a tragicomedy!)  , in this won position, Botvinnik accepted a draw against Model in the 1931 Leningrad Championship.  The path to victory is not complicated: }
2. Kc6 Bc8 3. Bc4 { Zugzwang. } 3... Bg4 4. Kb7 Bf3+ 5. Ka7
{ ∆ Ba6-b7+-   @@StartSquare@@Ed. The winning line runs  5...Be4  6.Ba6  Bf3  7.Bb7  Bg4  8.Bc6  Bc8  9.Bb5  Ke7  10.Ba6  after which the Black bishop can no longer stop the b-pawn.@@EndSquare@@ }
