{ Tragicomedies: Teichmann - Marshall, San Sebastian 1911  (analysis)   Let’s go back to the starting position of this endgame. Averbakh recommends }
1... Bb1 2. Bd3
{ White has greater practical chances here.   On  2.Bf1  Kf4  decides, for instance:  3.Kd4  f5!  ⨀  4.Kd5  Ke3  5.Ke6  Kf2  6.Bc4  Kxg2  , or @@StartFEN@@8/8/5p2/6p1/2K2k1p/5P1P/6P1/1b3B2 w - - 3 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Kd5  Kg3  4.Ke6  f5  5.Kf6  Kf2  6.Bc4  Kxg2  7.Kxg5  Kxh3  8.f4  Kg3  -+ }
2... Ba2+ 3. Kc5
{ Diagram 6-28   Averbakh contents himself with the single variation  3...Kf4  4.Kd4  Kg3  -+ But I think that  3...Kf4?  is an error, because of  4.Kd6!   @@StartBracket@@a@@EndBracket@@  4...Kg3  5.Ke7  Kxg2   5...f5  6.Kf6!  6.Kxf6  Kxf3  7.Kxg5  Kg3  now not  8.Bf5?  Bc4  , with ...Bf1xh3 to follow, but  8.Kf5!  Bd5   8...Kxh3  9.Kf4=  9.Bf1!   9.Ke5?  Bg2  10.Kd4  Bxh3  11.Ke3  Bc8  12.Bf1  Bb7  or  9.Be4?  Bc4  are both bad.  9...Bc6  10.Ke5  Bd7  11.Ke4  Kf2  12.Kf4  Be6  13.Bb5  Bxh3  14.Bc6  @@StartBracket@@reaching a position from Chéron’s line@@EndBracket@@  14...Bc8  15.Bb7!  Be6  16.Bd5!  , etc.   @@StartBracket@@b@@EndBracket@@  4...f5  5.Ke7  Bd5  6.Bf1!   6.Kf6?  is a mistake, in view of  6...g4  7.fxg4  fxg4  8.hxg4  Bxg2  9.g5  h3  10.g6  h2  11.g7  Bd5  -+  6...Ke5  7.Kd7  is not dangerous and neither is @@StartFEN@@8/4K3/8/3b1pp1/5k1p/5P1P/6P1/5B2 b - - 3 6@@EndFEN@@  6...g4  7.fxg4  fxg4  8.hxg4  Kxg4  9.Kf6  Be4   9...Kg3  10.Kg5  Bc6  11.Kh5=  10.Ke5!  Ba8  11.Kf6  Bb7  12.Kg6  Be4+  13.Kh6!=  but not  13.Kf6?  Kf4!  , when White is in zugzwang.  Black’s king stands very well on e5, where it shoulders aside the enemy king. Before attacking the g2-pawn, Black must first strengthen his position. }
3... f5
{ The simplest.   And  3...Be6!  4.Ba6  f5  5.Bf1  Bc8!?  or  5...Bd5  6.Be2  Bb7  7.Bf1  Kf4  8.Kd4  Bc8!  ⨀ -+ are not bad either. However, the hasty  5...g4?  would let slip the win:  6.fxg4  fxg4  7.hxg4  Bxg4  8.Ba6!   On  8.Kc4?  Bc8!  9.Kc3  Kf4  10.Kd2  Kg3  11.Ke3  Bd7!  ⨀ -+ or  11.Ke1  Bg4!  ⨀ -+, we get zugzwangs already familiar to us.  8...Be6  9.Bb7!  Bf5  10.Kc4  Be4  11.Bc8=  And if @@StartFEN@@8/8/B7/2K1k3/6bp/8/6P1/8 b - - 1 8@@EndFEN@@  8...Bf5  9.Kc4  . }
4. Kc6
{ 4.Bf1  Kf4  5.Kd4  Bb1  ⨀ and if  5.Kd6  Kg3  6.Ke5  Bb1  7.Kf6  Kf2  8.Bc4  Kxg2  9.Kxg5  Kxh3  -+ }
4... g4 5. fxg4 fxg4 6. hxg4 Bd5+ 7. Kc5 Bxg2 8. g5 h3 9. g6 Kf6
{ Black wins. } *

