{ Worse is  2...Bxg4?!  but Black can probably still defend after  3.f4+  Ke6  4.e4  Kd7   4...Ke7?  5.Bxd5  Bc8  6.Kc4!  +-  5.Bxd5  f6  6.Bxb7  h5  . }
3. g3 Bxg4 4. f4+ gxf4 5. gxf4+ { 5.exf4+  Ke6  6.Kd4  Bf3= } 5... Kf6 6. Bxd5
Bc8
{ 6...Ke7  7.Bxb7  h5  defends.   Ed. note: analyzed in the next variation → Diagram 6-30 and the game continuation is presented in Diagram 6-31. }
