{ Donner - Smyslov, Havana 1964  (continued) } 9... h4
{ Smyslov prepares the exchange of bishops. The immediate  9...Bd4?  leads only to a draw:  10.Bxd4  Kxd4  11.Kxd2  h4  12.g5! }
10. Bf2 Bc3 11. Bg1 Bd4 12. Bxd4
{ After  12.Bh2  Black sacrifices the bishop:  12...Ke3!  13.Bg1+  Kxf3  14.Bxd4  Kg2  15.Kxd2  Kxh3  16.g5  Kg2  17.Be5  h3  18.Ke3  h2  19.Bxh2  Kxh2  -+ }
12... Kxd4 13. Kxd2 Ke5 14. Ke3 g5 15. f4+ { 15.Ke2  Kf4  16.Kf2  f6  ⨀  -+ }
15... gxf4+ 16. Kf3 f6 17. Kf2 Ke4 18. Ke2 f3+ 19. Kf1 f2
{ The standard triangulation maneuver, as seen in the gameFahrni-Alapin, does not work here, since Black’s king does not have the f5-square available. }
20. Kxf2 { 20.Ke2  f1=Q+ } 20... Kf4 { Black wins. } *

