{ Bishop and Pawn vs. Knight   V. Bron, 1955   The outcome in all endgames of this sort depends wholly on whether the stronger side can place his opponent in zugzwang.   In the present case, this is possible. }
1. Bb3+ Kc5 { On  1...Ke5  2.Be6  ⨀  the game ends at once. } 2. Ba2 Kc6
{ 2...Ng4  3.Ke6 } 3. Ke6 Nh7 { 3...Kc5  4.Bb1  or  4.Bd5 } 4. Bd5+ Kc5 5. Ke7
Nf6 { 5...Nf8  6.Be4  ⨀  is no better. } 6. Bf3 Ng8+ 7. Ke6 Nf6 8. Be4
{ The decisive zugzwang! } *

