[SetUp "1"]

{ Let's put Black's king on e5. Now the variations are different, but the evaluation of the position does not change, and neither does the goal of White's maneuvers − zugzwang. }
1. Bb3 Kf5 2. Bf7 Kg5 { 2...Ke5  3.Be6  ⨀ } 3. Be6 Kg6 4. Kf8 Nh7+
{ 4...Kh6  5.Kf7  Kg5  6.Bh3  ⨀ } 5. Ke8 Nf6+ 6. Ke7
{ Zugzwang. In order to give his opponent the move, White has triangulated with his king. }
6... Kg7 7. Bf7 Ng4 8. Bd5 { But not  8.d7?  Ne5  9.d8=Q  Nc6+ } 8... Ne5
{ 8...Nf6  9.Be4!  Ng8+  10.Ke6  Nf6  11.Bf5  ⨀ } 9. Be4 Kg8 10. Ke6 Nf7 11. d7
Kf8 12. Bd5 Nd8+ 13. Kd6 { Zugzwang. } 13... Kg7 14. Ke7 { White wins. } *

