{ Now, in the diagrammed position, let's move White's king to c7. It is not hard to see that Black can draw this and not just with his knight on f6, but also on f8 or e5, which brings us to the conclusion:  For a successful defense, it is important to keep the knight far away from the enemy king. }
1. -- *

