{ 7/1. P. Seuffert, 1856 } 1. Bc3
{ Reciprocal zugzwang arises with the bishop on d4 and the king on b5 or d5. We have discussed an almost identical position, only moved one file to the right @@StartBracket@@seeDiagram 7-2@@EndBracket@@, where Black could successfully avoid a zugzwang. Here he fails to do so. }
1... Kb6 2. Ba5+ Kb5 3. Bd8 Kc5 4. Bg5 Kb5 { Diagram 16-59 } 5. Bh4
{ Zugzwang. This waiting move was not possible in the above-mentioned case: the edge of the board was closer. }
5... Kc5 6. Bf2+ Kd5 7. Bd4 { Zugzwang } 7... Nd6 8. c7 { White wins. } *

