{ Knight and Pawn vs. Bishop    The bishop is a strong piece, sometimes capable of preventing a pawn from queening even without the king's help. }
1... Be8
{ White threatened interference with @@StartFEN@@8/2K5/3P4/1b2N3/8/8/8/7k w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  2.Nc6  . }
2. Nd7 Kg2 3. Kd8 Bg6 4. Ke7 Bf5 5. Nc5 { ∆ Ne6 } 5... Bc8
{ Black was saved, first of all, because the pawn had not yet reached the seventh rank, and second, because the bishops diagonal was sufficiently long: five squares. Knight and king are only capable of interdicting two squares each, which leaves the fifth square free. }
*

