{ Tragicomedies: Smyslov – Gurgenidze, USSR ch, Tbilisi 1966    White wins, using exactly the same move @@StartBracket@@and the same technique@@EndBracket@@ as in the Chiburdanidze-Muresan game:  1.h4!  It is vital to fix the enemy pawn on the vulnerable h5-square, in order to tie one of Black’s pieces to its defense, or in some lines to create a dangerous passed h-pawn. }
1. Kd5 { In the game, White erred and the position became drawn. } 1... h4
{ If White sends his king after the a7-pawn, Black squeezes it into the corner with ...Kc7. And on g2-g3, Black exchanges pawns and easily blockades the passed g-pawn which results. Besides, he only needs to give up his knight for it, and then bring his king back to b8 @@StartBracket@@the elementary fortress already known to us@@EndBracket@@ to secure the draw. }
2. Be2 Nf8 3. Ke4 Kg5 4. Kd5 Kf6 5. Bg4 Ng6 { And the game ended in a draw. } *

