{ Nebylitsyn − Galuzin, USSR 1969  White's king is tied forever to the king's wing. The evaluation of this position hinges on whether the knight and pawns can erect an uncrossable barrier in the path of the enemy king. }
1... c4
{ A tempting, but incorrect pawn sacrifice. Black's goal is achieved by  1...Bd2!  2.Nb6  Ba5  3.Nc4  Bc7  when there appears to be nothing that can stop the transfer of the king to a6, followed by ...b7-b5. If  4.Na3  then  4...Kc8  5.Nb5  Bb8  followed by b7-b6 and ...Kb7-a6-a5. }
2. bxc4 Be3 3. a5 Bd2
{ Diagram 7-39   Or  3...Kc8  4.Nb6+  Kc7  5.Na8+  Kb8  6.Nb6  Bd2   In case of  6...Bc5  7.Nd7+  Ka7  8.Nxc5  dxc5  9.Kg1=  Ka6??  10.d6  +- and @@StartFEN@@1k6/1p6/1N1p4/P2Pp1p1/2P1Pp2/4bPpP/6K1/8 b - - 6 6@@EndFEN@@  6...Ka7  7.Nc8+  Ka6  8.Nxd6  +-  7.a6  and we're back in the game continuation.  Ed. note: continued in the next variation → Diagram 7-39 }
*

