{ Tragicomedies: Balashov – Smyslov, Tilburg 1977 } 1... Qa1
{ Black draws after  1...Qxe3!  2.fxe3  Nf8!  The knight moves inexorably to c5, from where it deprives the enemy king of the important squares d3 and e4  @@StartBracket@@barrier@@EndBracket@@; after this, Black plays ...Kg7-f6 and ...h7- h6.  3.Kf2  Nd7  4.Kf3  Nc5  5.Kg4  Kg6  is not dangerous, since there can be no bishop check from  d3  . If White’s king heads for the b-file, Black defends the knight with his king from  d6  . }
2. g3
{ ∆ 3.h4 and White won easily.   Diagram 7-42 has been intentionally omitted. }
