{ R. Réti, 1922 } 1. Nd4+ Kc5
{ In this line, Black needs just one tempo; therefore, with the king already at  c5  , this line would not work: @@StartFEN@@8/8/7b/P1k5/3N4/8/5PKp/8 w - - 0 2@@EndFEN@@  2.Nb3+?  Kb5  3.Kxh2  Bf4+  4.Kh3  Bb8  5.Kg4  Kb4=  Or  2.Kxh2?  Bf4+  3.Kh3  Kxd4  4.a6  Bb8= }
2. Kh1
{ Zugzwang. There is not one square for the bishop where it would not be vulnerable to a knight fork. }
