{ 7/13. Adapted from Gerusel-Kestler, BRD ch, Mannheim 1975 } 1... b5
{ Otherwise White plays @@StartFEN@@8/6p1/1p6/3n4/3Pk1p1/P7/5K2/4B3 w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  2.a4  and eventually a4-a5. But after this technically perfect solution, he is devoid of any counterchances. }
2. Kg3 Nf6 3. Bc3 g5 4. Bb2 Kf5 5. Ba1 Nh5+ 6. Kg2 Kg6
{ The king can go around, through h5, because White will not be able to push his d pawn. }
7. Bb2 { 7.d5  Nf4+  -+ } 7... Nf4+ 8. Kg3 Kh5 9. Ba1 Nd5 10. Bb2 Ne3 11. Bc3
Nf5+ 12. Kg2 Kh4 { Black wins. } *

