[SetUp "1"]

{ Zubarev − Alexandrov, Moscow 1915  (continued) } 1. Ng4
{ One more black pawn must now be moved to the same color square as its bishop. }
1... h5 2. Ne3 Bg6
{ 14...h4  15.gxh4  gxh4  16.Ng2  and if @@StartFEN@@8/2k2b2/p3p3/1pKpP1pp/8/2P1N1P1/PP5P/8 b - - 1 2@@EndFEN@@  14...g4  15.Ng2  followed by 16.Nf4. }
3. h4 { Fixing the pawns ! } 3... gxh4 4. gxh4 { ∆ Ng2-f4. } 4... Be4 5. Nf1
Bf3 6. Nd2 Be2 7. Nb3 Bg4 8. Nd4
{ Zugzwang.   The concluding phase of White's plan is to create a zugzwang position.  For this the knight needs to be brought to f4, tying the bishop to the defense of two pawns at once. }
8... Bh3 9. Ne2 Bf5 10. Nf4 Bg4 11. b4 { Zugzwang. The end is achieved! } 11...
Kd7 12. Kb6 Bf3 13. Kxa6 Kc6 14. Nxe6 { Black resigned. } *

