{ Karpov – Kasparov, Moscow wm  (9)  1984/85  (analysis)     White will not have an easy trip back: on  22.Kh6  , there follows  22...Kf6  , and Black’s king advances. White should continue with the text move. }
22. Nb8 Bc2 23. Nc6+ Ke6 { There are two ways to reach the goal: } 24. Ne5
{ If Black goes @@StartFEN@@3K4/4N3/4k3/1p1p4/1P1P4/P7/4b3/8 b - - 15 29@@EndFEN@@  29...Bf1  instead of 29...Kd6 then  30.Nc6  +- }
24... Kf5
{ After the passive  24...Ke7  25.Ng4  ,  White brings the knight to e3, then returns the king unhindered to its own side, and begins preparations for a3-a4, bringing the knight to c3 at the right moment. }
25. Kf7 Ke4 { 25...Bd1  26.Nc6!  Ke4  27.Ke6  +- } 26. Nc6 Bd1 27. Ke6
{ 27.Ke7?  Kd3  28.Kd6  Kc4  29.Ke5  Bf3  would be inexact. } 27... Bh5 28. Kd7
{ But not  28.Kd6?  Be8  29.Ne7  Kxd4  30.Nxd5  Kc4= } 28... Bg6
{ 28...Be2  29.Kd6  and 30.Kc5. In case of @@StartFEN@@8/3K4/2N5/1p1p3b/1P1Pk3/P7/8/8 b - - 13 28@@EndFEN@@  28...Kd3  29.a4! }
29. a4 bxa4 30. b5 a3 31. Nb4
