[SetUp "1"]

{ Moving Downstairs   First let us look at the rarest case, when a pawn is stronger than a rook.  G. Barbier, F. Saavedra, 1895 }
1. c7 Rd6+ 2. Kb5 { 2.Kc5?  Rd1= } 2... Rd5+ 3. Kb4 Rd4+ 4. Kb3 Rd3+ 5. Kc2
{ This maneuver, which helps the king to avoid checks, is what we call moving downstairs. However the fight is not over for the moment. }
5... Rd4 6. c8=R { If  6.c8=Q?  then  6...Rc4+  7.Qxc4  stalemate. } 6... Ra4
7. Kb3 { White wins. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
