[FEN "7K/6R1/1k6/p7/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Cutting the King Off } 1. Rg5
{ When the black pawn reaches a3 it will be eliminated by means of Rg3 @@StartBracket@@the pawn may even come to a2 and then perish after Rg1 followed by Ra1@@EndBracket@@.   @@StartSquare@@Ed. note: to illustrate the rule of cutting the king off on the fifth rank @@StartFEN@@7K/8/1k6/6R1/8/p7/8/8 w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.Rg3  a2  2.Ra3  +- and if that is not possible due to a different placement of the white rook, then  2.Rg1  as mentioned above, followed by 3.Ra1 is also enough for a win. The black king is too far.@@EndSquare@@ }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
