[SetUp "1"]

{ In the starting position, let us move the black king to c6 and the pawn to b5. }
1. Rg5 { Still the strongest move but Black can reply with } 1... Kb6
{ However, the king transfer to the a-file loses time, and its position is less favorable there than on the c-file @@StartBracket@@where it 'gives a shoulder kick' to the rival king@@EndBracket@@. }
2. Kg7 Ka5 3. Kf6 { White arrives in proper time to stop the pawn. } *

