{ Pawn Promotion to a Knight } 1. Rh2+ Kc1
{ Black can also save himself by stalemate:  1...Kb1!  2.Kb3  Ka1!  3.Rxb2  However, with a bishop or a central pawn his only drawing possibility is pawn-to-knight promotion. }
2. Kc3 b1=N+ 3. Kd3 Na3 4. Ra2 Nb1
{ It is worth mentioning that the erroneous  4...Nb5?  loses the knight.  In rook-versus-knight endings, one should not separate the knight from the king. }
*

