{ By the way, an additional pawn at b5 could not have helped Black. } 1. Kb4 a2
2. Kb3 a1=N+ 3. Kc3 b4+ 4. Kxb4 Nc2+ 5. Kc3 Ne3 6. Rh4
{ Another option is  6.Kd3  Nd5  7.Rh4  Kb2  8.Rd4  and the knight, being separated from the king, will die soon. }
6... Ka2
{ 6...Nd1+  7.Kd2  Nb2  8.Rb4  Ka2  9.Kc2  Ka1  10.Rb8  +-. And if  6...Nd5+  7.Kb3  Kc1  8.Rc4+  Kb1  9.Rd4  +-. }
7. Ra4+ Kb1 8. Re4 Nf5 9. Re5 Nd6 10. Kb3 Kc1 11. Rc5+ Kb1 12. Rd5
{ White wins. } *

