{ Outflanking   Shouldering and outflanking ideas are distinctly represented in the following famous endgame study.  R. Réti, 1928 }
1. Rd2
{ 1.Rd3  is equally good. But  1.Rd1?  is erroneous:  1...d4  2.Kf7  Ke4  3.Ke6  d3  , and if @@StartFEN@@8/4K3/8/4k3/3p4/8/8/3R4 w - - 0 2@@EndFEN@@  2.Kd7  Kd5!  (Black prevents an outflanking)  3.Kc7  Kc5!  and it is White who has fallen into zugzwang.  3...Kc4?  would run into  4.Kd6  d3  5.Ke5  +- }
1... d4 2. Rd1 Kd5 3. Kd7 { Black is in zugzwang. } 3... Kc4
{ And if  3...Ke4  then  4.Kc6  +- } 4. Ke6 { White wins. } *

