{ Tragicomedies: Neumann – Steinitz, Baden Baden 1870 } 1. Kf8
{ The simplest way is  1.Kg8!  Kg6  2.Kh8= } 1... Kf6 2. g8=N+ Ke6 3. Nh6 Rh7
4. Ng4
{ As we already know, after  4.Ng8!  the game would have been drawn. Now White is lost. }
4... Rh4 { 4...Rh3!  could have won immediately. } 5. Ne3 { 5.Nf2  Rf4+ } 5...
Re4 6. Nd1 Rf4+ 7. Kg7 Rf3 8. Kg6
{ 8.Nb2  Kd5  9.Na4  Rb3  ∆  10.--  Kd4  and  11.--  Rb4  makes no difference. }
8... Ke5 9. Kg5 Kd4 10. Kg4 Rf1 11. Nb2 Rb1 12. Na4 Rb4 { White resigned. } *

