{ 8/2. J. Moravec, 1913 } 1. Kh7
{ In case of  1.Kxg7?  h4  2.Kg6  h3  3.Kg5  h2  4.Kg4  h1=Q  White is forced to play  5.Ra1+  because after  5.Kg3??  Qh8  . Therefore the g7-pawn should be left alone. }
1... h4
{ After  1...g5!?  2.Kg6  g4  , the primitive  3.Kxh5?  g3  4.Kg4  g2  5.Kh3  Kh1!  leads only to a draw. In order to avoid stalemate, the h5-pawn should not be captured:  3.Kg5!! }
2. Kg6 h3 3. Kg5 h2 4. Kg4 h1=Q
{ 4...g5!?  5.Kg3  h1=N+  6.Kf3  g4+  7.Kxg4  Nf2+  8.Kf3  does not help because the knight will be caught soon @@StartBracket@@seeDiagram 8-5@@EndBracket@@. }
5. Kg3 { White wins. } *

