[White "Chapter 8 – Rook versus Pawns"]
[Black "Diagram 8-17 Exercise 8/4"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "5K2/p7/8/8/8/k3p3/8/6R1 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ 8/4. V. Sokov, 1940 } 1. Rb1
{ The routine  1.Ke7?  misses a win in view of  1...Kb4!  2.Re1  (Otherwise 2...Kc3)  2...a5  3.Kd6  a4  and the black king applies a shouldering to the white opponent. The move ...Kb4! should be prevented. }
1... Ka2
{ 1...a5  2.Ke7  a4  3.Kd6  Ka2  4.Re1  a3  5.Kc5  Kb2  and here both  6.Kb4  a2  7.Re2+  Kc1  8.Rxa2  Kd1  9.Kc3  +- and  6.Re2+  Kb1   6...Kb3  7.Rxe3+  7.Kb4  a2  8.Kb3  +-  are strong. }
2. Re1 a5 3. Ke7 Kb3
{ Diagram 16-68   We know already what happens after  3...a4  4.Kd6  . } 4. Kd6
{ Rather than  4.Rxe3+?  Kb4  5.Kd6  a4  6.Re4+  Kb5!  with a draw @@StartBracket@@shouldering again!@@EndBracket@@. }
4... a4 { 4...Kb4  5.Kd5  a4  6.Kd4  a3  7.Rb1+  +- } 5. Kc5 a3 6. Rxe3+ Ka4
{ 6...Kb2  7.Kb4  a2  8.Re2+  Kb1  9.Kb3  +- } 7. Kc4 a2 8. Re1 Ka3 9. Kc3
{ White wins. } *

