[FEN "8/4K3/8/4p3/8/4k3/6R1/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ 8/5. Y. Averbakh, 1980 } 1. Ke6
{ The premature  1.Rg5?  leads only to a draw after  1...Kf4!  2.Kf6  e4=   1.Kd6?  is also incorrect:  1...e4  2.Rg5  Kd3  or  2...Kd2!   As well as  1.Kf6?  e4  2.Rg5  Kf2  or  2...Kf3!  because the outflanking technique cannot be applied. }
1... e4 2. Rg5
{ Only this move wins. White places his rook behind the passed pawn with tempo and, after Black moves his king out of the way, the white king outflanks it from the opposite side. }
2... Kd2
{ 2...Kd3  is similar to the text, while  2...Ke2  3.Ke5  e3  4.Ke4  , and in case of  2...Kf3  or  2...Kf2  3.Rf5+!  Kg2  4.Re5!  Kf3  5.Kd5!  +- }
3. Rd5+ Kc2 4. Re5 Kd3 5. Kf5 { White wins. } *

