{ Rook vs. Connected Pawns    If two black pawns are placed on the third rank, or one pawn has reached the second rank while the other is on the fourth rank, a rook cannot stop them.  Sometimes, however, White can save himself by creating  checkmate threats , when the black king is pressed to an edge of the board. }
1. -- *

