{ Tragicomedies: Sax – Tseshkovsky, Rovinj/Zagreb 1975 } 1. Rh3+
{ He should not move the rook away from the d-file where it was protecting the king from side checks. An easy win was  1.f7!  Rc8  2.Ke7  Rc7+  3.Rd7  +- In case of @@StartFEN@@8/5P1k/4K3/8/8/3R4/8/2r5 b - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...Kg7  2.Rg3+  and if  1...Re1+  2.Kf6  Rf1+  3.Ke7  Re1+  4.Kf8  Ra1  5.Rh3+  Kg6  6.Kg8  +- }
1... Kg6 2. Rg3+
{ Black resigned, as he failed to recognize that the position had become drawn:  2...Kh7  3.f7  and now not  3...Rc6+?  4.Kd7  +-, but @@StartFEN@@8/5P1k/4K3/8/8/6R1/8/2r5 b - - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3...Rc8!  4.Rd3  Kg7=  . And if after  3...Rc8!  4.Ke7  then  4...Rc7+  5.Ke8  Rc8+  6.Kd7  Ra8=  . }
