{ 9/2. N. Kopaev, 1958 } 1... Kf6
{ Black should take measures against strengthening White's position after Ke8 and e6-e7. If  2.e7+  now, then  2...Kf7=   1...Rb1?  loses to  2.e7  Rb7+  3.Ke6  Rb8  4.Rd6  and 5.Rd8 +-. }
