{ The Pawn on the Fifth Rank   This is the so-called  Philidor position.  The famous French chess player was the first to demonstrate, as early as the 18th century, the correct method of defense. }
1... Rb6 { Preventing a penetration of the white king to the sixth rank. } 2.
e6 Rb1
{ If the pawn stood at e5, the white king would have had a  refuge  from vertical checks. But, as soon as the pawn has stepped forward, the refuge does not exist anymore. }
