{ Tragicomedies: Lobron – Knaak, Baden Baden 1992 } 1... Kxe3
{ To avoid the theoretical draw, Black should have played  1...Kd3!  The white king is placed at the long side, and one cannot see how White can survive, for example  2.Rd5+  Kxe3  3.Kc2  Ke2!?   3...Rxg3  4.Re5!?  Kf4  5.Re8  Rd3!  -+, or  5.Rd5  Kf3  6.Re5  e3  7.Kd3  Kf2  -+ is also playable.  4.Rd2+  Kf3  5.Rd7  , and now either  5...Rf8!?  6.Kd1  Kf2!  7.Rd2+  Kf1  -+ or  5...Rxg3  6.Re7  e3  7.Kd3  Kf2  -+ followed by Rf3-f8. }
2. Kc2 Rxg3 3. Re8 Rg2+
{ Draw, according to the seconddefensive method in the Philidor position. } *

