{ 9/4. Vukic-Klaus Uwe Müller, Varna 1975 } 1... Kf8
{ Black holds by means of transferring his king to the short side.   Black chose the incorrect continuation  1...Ra6?  2.Kg7!  The f-pawn will be lost anyway and the king will forever remain on the long side where it only obstructs his own rook. The remainder was  2...Rc6  3.Rb8+  Ke7  4.Rb1  Ra6  5.Re1+  Kd8  6.Kf7  Kd7  7.Rd1+  Kc7  8.Ke7  Black resigned. }
2. Rb6 { 2.Kxf6  Ra6+  and  2.Rb8+  Ke7=  ∆ ...Rg4+. } 2... Rf4
{ @@StartFEN@@1R6/7k/5K2/5P2/6r1/8/8/8 w - - 3 5@@EndFEN@@ Here, however, Black holds because of the fact that he has two files @@StartBracket@@a- and b-@@EndBracket@@ for his rook to stay far away from the white king. The white rook occupies one of them, but Black can use the remaining one:  5.Ke6  Re4+  6.Kf7  Ra4 = }
3. Kxf6 { 3.Rxf6+  Kg8  4.Ra6  Rg4+= } 3... Kg8 4. Rb8+ Kh7 5. Ke6
{ 5.Rf8  Ra4= } 5... Kg7 { Draw. } *

