{ Tragicomedies: A.Zaitsev – Hübner, Büsum 1969 } 1... Rb1
{ A draw could have been achieved with  1...Rb4  2.f5  Rb1!  3.Kh5  Rg1!   The waiting tactic with  1...Ra5  was quite good too: after  2.g5  fxg5+  3.fxg5  , Black could defend the position either in the Philidor method  3...Ra6  , or passively  3...Ra8  . And if White would play @@StartFEN@@6k1/3R4/5p2/r7/5PPK/8/8/8 w - - 0 2@@EndFEN@@  2.f5  , then  2...Ra1! }
2. Kh5 Rg1 { Otherwise 3.Kg6. } 3. g5 fxg5 4. f5 Kf8 5. f6 { Black resigned. }
