{ In the initial position, the rook is placed best at c8 where it prevents a pawn advance. However, Black holds with a rook at h8, too. }
1. c5 Rh4
{ Cutting the king off the pawn.   1...Ke7  draws as well  2.Kc4  Rd8= } 2. c6
Ke7 3. c7 Rh8
{ Horizontally cutting the king off from the pawn is a useful defensive method.   Another important tip:  in this sort of position, the black king should stay on the fifth or sixth rank.  If he does not, Black usually loses. }
