1... Kd5 2. Ra6 Rb7 { Or  2...Kd4 } 3. Ka4 Kc4 4. Rc6+ Kd5 5. b5
{ Conclusion:  cutting off the king of the weaker side along a rank can often be more effective than the same procedure along a file. }
