{ The Rook Is in Front of the Pawn and the Pawn Is on the Seventh Rank   A standard defensive formation: Black's rook is behind the hostile pawn, while the king is placed on g7 or h7. White's rook is riveted to the pawn and cannot leave a8. }
1. Kb6 Rb1+
{ The white king cannot escape from vertical checks. Black's rook drives the king away and returns to a1. }
