{ Back to the last diagram; let's add a white pawn on h5. For the outcome, there will be no change: Black simply ignores its existence. @@StartFEN@@R7/P5k1/8/2K3P1/6P1/6P1/8/r7 w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@ The same is valid for a g5-pawn and even for two or three white pawns on the g-file.   However, an f5-pawn wins. }
1. f6+ Kf7 { 1...Kxf6  2.Rf8+  and if  1...Kh7  2.f7  +- } 2. Rh8
{ And Black loses his rook. } *

