[SetUp "1"]

{ Ivanchuk – Lautier, Horgen 1995 } 1... Rb4
{ The Vancura position could be achieved through the elementary  1...Rf6!  2.Ra8+  Kxh7  3.Kxb2  Kg7  . After  2.Kxb2  Black’s rook would become “desperado” because his king is stalemated. }
2. Rc7 { 2.Rb7  is also good. } 2... Ra4 3. Rc8+
{ White gives his adversary a nice present: a vitally important tempo  3.a7??  Rxa7=  was obviously erroneous, but the line @@StartFEN@@7k/2R4P/P7/8/r7/8/1p6/1K6 w - - 3 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Rc6!  Kxh7  4.Kxb2  Kg7  5.Kb3  Ra1  6.Kb4  Kf7  7.Kb5  or  7.Kc5  Ke7  8.Kb6  Kd7  9.Kb7  led to a win. }
3... Kxh7 4. Rc6 Rb4
{ A gift in return! After  4...Kg7!  , Black’s king could have come to the queenside in time:  5.Kxb2  Kf7  6.Kb3  Ra1  7.Kb4  Ke7  8.Kb5  Kd7= }
5. a7 Ra4 6. Rc7+ Kg6 7. Kxb2 Kf6 8. Kb3 Ra1 9. Kb4 Ke6 10. Kb5 { 10.Kc5 }
10... Kd6 11. Rc6+ { 11.Rh7 } 11... Kd5 12. Ra6 Rb1+ 13. Ka5 Kc5 14. Rc6+ Kxc6
15. a8=Q+ { And White won. } *

