{ a- and h-Pawns   In the Vancura position, let us add a white pawn on the h-file. It is easy to see that the evaluation remains unchanged. The defensive method is precisely the same as before: the rook maintains the pawn in the crosshairs from the side and does not release the hostile rook from the corner. }
1... Re4+ 2. Kd3 Re5 3. Kc4 Rf5
{ The best policy is to pay no attention to the h-pawn at all.  3...Rxh5?  loses to  4.a6  Rh6  5.Kb5  Rh5+  6.Kb6  Rh6+  7.Kb7  +- }
4. a6 { 4.Kb4  Rf4+= } 4... Rf6 5. Kb5 Rf5+ 6. Kc6 Rf6+ 7. Kd5 Rb6 { etc. } *

