{ Tragicomedies: Suetin – F. Portisch, Belgrade 1977    White could move his rook to a more advantageous position:  1.Rb5+  or  1.Rc5!  Kb6  2.Rc3  Rf4  3.Rh3  +- In case of @@StartFEN@@8/8/1k6/8/7P/P1R2r2/1K6/8 b - - 3 2@@EndFEN@@  2...Rf2+  3.Rc2!?  ∆ 4.Rh2, or  3.Kb3  Rh2  4.Rc4  and 5.a4 with an easy win. However Suetin does not suspect any danger of a draw. }
1. a4 Rf4 2. Kb3 Ka6 { The threat was 3.Rb5+ followed by 4.h5 +- } 3. a5 Re4 4.
Kc3 Rf4 5. Kd3 Rg4 6. Ke3 Rc4 7. Kf3 Rc3+
{ The rook is placed best on the c-file.  7...Rb4?  loses to  8.Rh8  Ka7  9.h5  Rb5  10.h6  +- }
8. Ke4 Rc4+ 9. Kd5 Rg4 10. Ke6 Rc4 11. Rh8 Kb7 12. Rh7+ Ka6 { Draw. } *

