{ Connected Pawns   Two extra connected pawns can be most easily exploited if the king supports them. However, sometimes they can advance for queening even when a rook alone supports them, as in this diagram.   Szabó − Keres, Moscow 1956 }
1. Rg6
{ White is planning 2.h6, 3.g5, 4.Rg7, 5.h7 etc. This simple plan cannot be prevented. Such pawns are sometimes called  self-propelled. }
1... Ke4 2. h6 Rh2 3. g5 Kd3 4. Rg7 Kc3 5. h7 { ∆ g6, Rg8 } 5... Kb3 6. Rb7+
{ Black resigned. } *

