{ 9/7. Spiridonov-Shamkovich, Polanica-Zdroj, 1970 } 1. Ra4
{ The natural looking  1.Rb6?  meets a brilliant refutation:  1...Rf4!!  2.exf4  a2  3.Kf3  Kh5  4.Ra6  b3  -+ The line  1.Kd2?  Rf2+  2.Kc1  a2  is hopeless; the same may be said about  1.Kd3?  Rf2  2.Kc4  Rb2  @@StartBracket@@“selfpropelled pawns”@@EndBracket@@  3.e4  a2  4.e5  Kg5  . Finally, if  1.e4?  the simplest is  1...Rb7  2.Kd2  b3  3.Kc1  b2+  4.Kb1  Rb3  ∆ 5...Rc3 -+. }
1... Rb7 2. Kd3 { Or  2.Kd2  . } 2... Kg3 3. Kc2 { ∆ 4.Kb3= } 3... b3+ 4. Kb1
a2+ 5. Kb2
