{ Tragicomedies: Polugaevsky – Ree, Amsterdam 1981 } 1. Ra8
{ The simplest way is to keep the rook on h8, in order to profit by the side checks in case of an emergency. }
1... Rg2+ 2. Ka3 Kc3 3. Rxa4
{ It was still not too late to bring the rook to the long side, for example  3.Rh8!?  c4  4.Rh3+  Kd2  5.Kb4!=  However this capture does not lose, contrary to comments by Krnic in the Chess Informant. }
3... c4 4. Ra8 Rg7 5. Ka2
{ This is the decisive error! Now the black king advances while the white rook remains chained to the a-file. He should have followed a waiting policy:  5.Ra6!  Rd7  6.Ra8  Kc2  7.Rh8!  and if @@StartFEN@@R7/3r4/8/8/2p5/K1k5/8/8 b - - 5 6@@EndFEN@@  6...Rd1  7.Ka2  Kc2  8.Rh8  c3  9.Rh2+  with a draw. }
5... Kc2 6. Ka1 c3 7. Ka2 Rb7 8. Ra6 Rd7 9. Ra8 Kd2 { White resigned. } *

