{ The rook that blocks a passed pawn cannot, as a rule, leave its post unpunished. Therefore it would have been wise to play for zugzwang:  1.Ra2!?  Kf5  2.e4+  Ke5  3.Ke3  , and now  3...Rc5  4.Kd3  , and if  3...Ra8  4.a5  Rh8  5.Ra4  or  5.Rf2  .   Another winning method was  1.Ke2  @@StartBracket@@∆ Kd3-c4-b4@@EndBracket@@  1...Ke4  2.Rf1!  ∆ Rf4+ @@StartFEN@@8/8/8/r7/P3k3/4P3/4K3/R7 w - - 2 2@@EndFEN@@  2.Rh1  is also fine as long as after  2...Rh5!  White plays  3.Rf1! }
