{ Tragicomedies: J. Polgar – Short, Monaco bl 1993 } 1... Re7
{ After the waiting move  1...Rb7  , the position is still drawn:  2.Ke6  Rb4  or  2...Rb1  3.Rd7+  Kh6  4.Kf5  Rb5+  5.Kxf6  Rb4!  6.g5+   6.Kf5  Rf4+  or  6...Rxg4  leads to stalemate.  6...Kxh5  7.Rh7+  Kg4  8  g6  Rb6+  9.Kf7  Rb7+  10.Kg8  Rb8+  11.Kg7  Kg5=  @@StartBracket@@Müller@@EndBracket@@. Short decided to at least prevent the king from invading at  e6  , but the cure proved worse than the disease – his resourceful adversary found an elegant forced win. }
2. h6+ Kf7 { 2...Kxh6  3.Kxf6  +- } 3. g5 fxg5 4. Rd8 { And Black resigned. } *

