{ Tragicomedies: Hebden − Wood, Hastings 1994/95 } 1... Kxf4
{ A terrible error! The black king will be cut off along the f-file now, and the g7-pawn will be inevitably lost.   The simplest way to a draw was  1...Kg6  2.Kg4  Ra4  3.Rd6+  Kf7=  And in case of  2.f5+  Kxf5  3.Rxg7  Ra1  4.Rf7+  Kg6=   Another possibility was  1...g6  2.Rf7+  Ke4  3.Rf6  Ra1  4.Kg3  Rg1+  5.Kh2  Rg4  , while after @@StartFEN@@8/5R2/6p1/6P1/4kP1K/r7/8/8 w - - 2 3@@EndFEN@@  3.f5  gxf5  4.g6  f4  5.g7  Rg3=  In case of  3.Kg4  , then  3...Ra1  4.Re7+  Kd5  5.Rg7  Ke4!  6.Rxg6  Rg1+  and after  7.Kh4??  Kf3!  White's king will be mated. }
2. Rf7+ Ke5 3. Kh5 Ra6 4. Rxg7 Ra5 5. Re7+ Kf5 6. Rf7+ Ke6 7. Rf1 Ra8 8. g6
Rh8+ 9. Kg5 Ke7 10. Re1+ { 10.g7  +- } 10... Kf8 11. Kf6 Rh6
{ 11...Rh7!?  12.Re8+! } 12. Re2 { Black resigned. } *

