{ This is a very important type of position. The black king stands in front of connected passed pawns but the white rook is placed behind Black's passed pawn. In such cases, the chances of the defender are minimal. However, this position can be saved if Black is on move. }
1... a2 2. h5 Kh7 { But by no means  2...Kh6??  3.Ra7!  ⨀ +- } 3. Kg5 Rg1 4.
Ra7+ Kg8 5. Rxa2 Rxg3+
{ The happy end resulted from the fact that one of the pawns had been standing on the third rank. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
