{ If White is on move, he succeeds in advancing the pawn and wins without difficulty. }
1. Kg5 a2 2. g4 Kf7 3. h5 Kg7 4. Ra7+ Kf8 5. h6 Kg8 6. Kg6
{ Black has no time for  6...Rg1  on account of the threatened mate.   If the pawn is on  g2  , White wins no matter who is on move. He simply advances his king and the h-pawn. The riposte @@StartFEN@@8/6k1/8/R7/6KP/8/p5P1/r7 b - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...Rg1  is useless because the white rook, capturing the a2-pawn,  2.Rxa2  , will protect the g2-pawn. }
*

