{ Finally, Black has no draw against the following White setup: pawns on h3-g4 and king on h4. }
1... a2 2. Ra6 Kh7 3. g5 Kg7 4. Kh5 Rh1 5. Ra7+ Kf8 { Or  4...Kg8 } 6. Rxa2
Rxh3+ 7. Kg6 { A winning endgame with a g-pawn arises. } *

