{ 9/15. G. Levenfish, V. Smyslov, 1957  This position resembles the endingTarrasch-Chigorin, but the solution is completely different. }
1... Ra1
{ ∆  2.--  a2  . Black holds because White cannot remove the f-pawn from the third rank in time.   The attempt  1...Rb2?  loses after  2.Ra4  a2  and here not  3.Kf4??  Rb4+  , but @@StartFEN@@8/6k1/8/8/R5P1/4KP2/pr6/8 w - - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Ra6  Kf7  4.f4  or  4.g5  , etc. }
2. Kf4 a2 3. Ra4 Kg6
{ Or  3...Kf7  , but not  3...Kf6?  4.Ra7!  ⨀  4...Ke6  or  4...Kg6  5.g5  ⨀ +- − Pogosyan. }
4. Ra6+ { 4.Ra7  Kf6  5.g5+  Kg6=  and White is in zugzwang. } 4... Kg7 5. g5
Kf7 6. Kf5 Rf1 7. Ra7+ Kg8 8. Rxa2 Rxf3+ 9. Kg6 Rf8 { Draw. } *

