{ Disconnected Pawns, One of Them Is Passed    If one or two files separate pawns of the stronger side, the position is most often a draw.  We shall analyze cases of more interest and practical value here: when the distance between pawns is great enough.  The defender must aspire for active counterplay. If his rook must merely defend his own pawn or protect the king from checks, his salvation is very problematic. }
1. -- *

