{ A typical method of bringing home a material advantage is the protection of all of ones pawns by the rook from the side.   Tsouros − Minev, Greece − Bulgaria m tt 1973 }
1... Rd5
{ Black wants to play ...b6-b5; thereafter the king, being released from its troubles with the g5-pawn, will set off for the queenside. White is helpless against this simple plan. Other setups are much less efficient. }
2. Rf7+ { 2.Re7  b5  3.Re8  Re5 } 2... Ke4 3. Rb7 b5 4. Kg4 Kd4 5. Kf3
{ 5.Kh5  Kc4  6.g4  b4  7.Rc7+  Rc5  is equally hopeless. } 5... Kc4 6. Ke4 Rc5
7. Rd7 b4 8. Rd1 b3 9. Rb1 Kc3 10. Rc1+ Kb4 11. Rb1 Rc4+ 12. Kf5 g4 13. Kg5 Kc3
{ White resigned. } *

