{ Marshall − Capablanca, New York  (9)  1909  (analysis)   The plan of transferring the rook to b4 is nevertheless correct. However, as Igor Zaitsev has noted, it has to be implemented somewhat differently. }
1... Rc6
{ Leads to the draw @@StartBracket@@preventing the white king from advancing to the center@@EndBracket@@. }
2. h4 Rb6 { Threatening  3.--  Rb4= } 3. h5 Rh6 4. Rh4 { Diagram 9-109 } 4...
Ka3 5. Kg7 Rxh5
{ The rook sacrifice did not work a move earlier; Black had to wait until the king was on g7. }
6. Rxh5 Kxa4 7. Kf6 Kb4 { Draw. } *

