{ Taimanov − Averbakh, Leningrad 1947  (continued) } 1... Rh6
{ As is known, the one who wins errs next to last @@StartBracket@@White's decisive error is still to come@@EndBracket@@. Black should have played  4...Rf7!  5.Rg4+  Kb5  6.Rg3  Ra7  7.Kf5  a3  8.Kg6  a2  9.Rg1  Kc4  etc. }
2. Rg4+ Kb3 3. Rg3+ Kc2 4. Rg2+ Kd3 5. Rg3+ Kc4 6. Rg4+ Kb5 7. Rxg7
{ The elementary  10.Kd4!  led to an immediate draw. The capture is much weaker because Black maintains the possibility of interference with his rook along the sixth rank. }
7... a3 8. Ra7
{ 11.Rg1  Rxh5+  12.Kd4  Kb4  13.Rb1+  Ka4  14.Kc3  a2  15.Rg1  Ka3  -+ } 8...
Ra6 9. Rb7+
{ 12.Rg7  a2  13.Rg1  did not help:  13...Rh6!  14.Kd4  Kb4  , and if @@StartFEN@@8/8/7r/1k2K2P/8/8/p7/6R1 w - - 2 11@@EndFEN@@  14.Ra1  Rxh5+  15.Kd4  Rh2  16.Kc3  Ka4  -+ }
9... Ka4 10. Rg7 Ra5+ 11. Kf6 a2 12. Rg4+ Kb3 { 15...Kb5??  16.Rg1= } 13. Rg3+
Kc4 14. Rg4+ Kd3 15. Rg3+ Ke4 16. Rg4+ Ke3 { 19...Kf3 } 17. Rg1 Rxh5 18. Rg3+
Kd4 19. Ra3 Rh2 20. Kf5 Rf2+ 21. Kg4 Kc4 { And White resigned soon. } *

