{ Four Pawns vs. Three on the Same Wing   If all pawns are on the same wing, bringing the advantage home is frequently impossible @@StartBracket@@it is more precise to say, it should not be possible against correct defense@@EndBracket@@. The fewer pawns, the easier the defense is.  For example, with three pawns against two or even with four against three, with standard pawn structures, the task of the defender is not too difficult @@StartBracket@@once in a lightning tournament I managed to hold two such endings, one against Tal and the other against Vasiukov@@EndBracket@@. As for the case of five pawns against four, the probability of losing is much greater. }
1. -- *

