{ Tragicomedies:Capablanca-Yates fully fits this category, but I would like to add some new examples, the last of which has some theoretical value.  Bellón – Chekhov, Barcelona 1984    The waiting policy,  1.Ra5  or  1.Rb7  , gave a rather easy draw, but Bellón decided to chase after the g7-pawn. }
1. Rb8+ Ke7 2. Rg8 Rd8
{ White resigned. The pawn endgame is quite hopeless for him, while after the text move, his rook is lost. }
3. Rxg7 Kf8 4. Rh7 Kg8 5. Rxh6 Kg7 6. Kg5 Rd5+ { Black wins. } *

