{ Piket – Kasparov, Internet Tournament 2000  (analysis)     Let us look at  6...Re4  , instead of  6...Ra2  . }
6... Re4
{ Diagram 9-128  This position has occurred in the following games: Stean-Hartston @@StartBracket@@Great Britain ch, Brighton 1972@@EndBracket@@, Ionov-Karasev @@StartBracket@@Leningrad 1983@@EndBracket@@ and Matveeva-Rappoport @@StartBracket@@Baku 1983@@EndBracket@@. In all these games, White found a forced win. }
7. e6 Rxe6 8. Rxe6 fxe6 9. h3 Kf7 10. Kh6 Kf6 11. g4 h4
{ 11...hxg4  12.hxg4  +- } 12. g5+ { 12.Kh7?  g5= } 12... Kf5 13. Kg7 Kxf4 14.
Kxg6 e5 15. Kf6 e4 16. g6 e3 17. g7 e2 18. g8=Q e1=Q 19. Qg4+ Ke3 20. Qe6+ Kf2
21. Qxe1+ Kxe1 22. Kg5 { White wins. } *

