{ Tragicomedies: Em.Lasker – Levenfish, Moscow 1925 } 1. g4
{ Lasker aspires for counterplay on the kingside. An alternative method was  1.Ke4  Ke7  2.Kd4  , trying to prevent the black king from joining his pawn. However  2...Rd8+!  was strong then. }
1... hxg4+
{ Levenfish lets the white king go ahead for no reason whatsoever. An easy win was  1...Ke7  2.gxh5  gxh5  , for example,  3.Ke4  Kd7  4.f5  Kc6  5.f6  Kb5  6.Ra1  a4  7.Kf4  Rg8  -+, or @@StartFEN@@r7/4kp2/4p3/p3P2p/R4P1P/5K2/8/8 w - - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.f5  exf5  4.Kf4  Ke6  5.Kg5  Kxe5  6.Kxh5  Kf6!  with inevitable mate. }
2. Kxg4 Ke7 3. Kg5 Ra7 4. Kh6 Kd7 5. Kg7 Kc6
{ Ed. note: continued in the next variation → Diagram 9-137 } *

