[SetUp "1"]

{ Tragicomedies: Em.Lasker − Levenfish, Moscow 1925  (continued) } 6. Kf6
{ A decisive loss of a tempo! Lasker saw the correct way but, as he explained after the game, he wanted instinctively to avoid a discovered check along the seventh rank.   He should have performed the breakthrough that gave him a passed pawn immediately:  6.f5!  gxf5  7.h5  , and if  6...exf5  7.e6  fxe6+  8.Kxg6  . After  8...Kb5  9.Ra1  f4  10.h5  , both  A.  10...f3  11.Rf1  a4  12.Rxf3  a3  13.Rf1  a2  14.Ra1  Kc4  15.h6  Kb3  16.h7  Ra8  17.Re1!  Kb2  18.Re2+  and if  17...e5  18.Kg7  e4  19.h8=Q  Rxh8  20.Kxh8  @@StartBracket@@the black pawn cannot reach  e2  , so there is no win@@EndBracket@@.  B.  10...e5  11.Re1!  Kc4   11...a4  12.Rxe5+  Kc6  13.Re4  a3  14.Rxf4  a2  15.Rf1=  12.Rxe5  Kd3  13.h6  f3  14.h7  Ra8  15.Rxa5  , and if  14...Rxh7  15.Kxh7  f2  16.Rf5  Ke3  17.Rf8   Or  17.Re5+  Kf4  18.Re8  17...a4  18.Re8+  Kf3  19.Rf8+  Kg2  20.Rg8+  Kh3  21.Rf8=  lead to a draw. }
6... Kb5 7. Ra1 a4 8. f5 exf5 9. e6 fxe6 10. Kxg6 f4 11. h5 f3 12. h6
{ 12.Rf1  a3  -+ } 12... e5 13. Re1
{ Neither  13.h7  Ra8  or  13...Rxh7  14.Kxh7  e4  15.Rf1  a3  16.Kg6  a2  17.Kf5  e3  18.Ke4  e2  -+ nor @@StartFEN@@8/r7/6KP/1k2p3/p7/5p2/8/R7 w - - 0 13@@EndFEN@@  13.Kf5  Rh7  14.Rh1  f2  15.Kxe5  Rxh6  -+ can help White. }
13... a3 14. Rxe5+ Kc4 15. Re1 a2 16. h7 Ra8
{ The pawns are separated by four files. Therefore  16...Rxh7?  17.Kxh7  f2  18.Rf1  Kd3  19.Ra1!  Kc3  20.Rf1!  would have enabled White to reach a draw. }
17. Kg7 f2 18. Rf1 { 18.Ra1  Kb3  -+ } 18... a1=Q+ 19. Rxa1 Rxa1 20. h8=Q Rg1+
{ White resigned.  Diagram 9-138 has been intentionally omitted. } *

