{ Rovner − Shchipunov, Kiev 1938  (sides reversed) } 1. b7
{ As we have just seen, Black inevitably loses his f-pawn. But, in contrast to the previous example, White fails to get a passed f-pawn.  1.Kd4  is not met by  1...Rxf2?  but by  1...h5= }
1... Kg7 2. Kd4 Rb5 3. Kc4 Rb2 4. Kd5 Rd2+ 5. Ke5 Re2+ 6. Kxf5 Rxf2+ 7. Kxg4
Rb2
{ Even two extra pawns cannot bring the advantage home. The game was drawn. } *

