{ Tragicomedies: Pähtz − Kosteniuk, Mainz m  (5)  2002    The main distinction between this position and the very similar endgameBenko-Gereben @@StartBracket@@Diagram 9-140@@EndBracket@@, is that here White has a pawn at  f3  , thanks to which every possible pawn endgame is won. An elementary path to victory lay in  1.Rd8!  Rb6+  2.Rd6  Rxb7  3.Rd7+  Rxd7  4.Kxd7  +- }
1. Re8 Rb6+ 2. Kf5 Rxb7
{ The position has now become drawn − but the adventures have not ended yet. }
