{ Tragicomedies: Pähtz − Kosteniuk, Mainz m  (5)  2002  (continued) } 1... Rc3
{ 7...Kg8!  8.Kg6  Rf8=  was necessary. As we know, against a knight pawn, passive defense by the rook on the eighth rank guarantees a draw. }
2. Kh5
{ After  8.Kg6!  White must reach the'Lucena Position', for example,  8...Rc6+  9.Kh7  Rc5  10.Rg7  +- }
2... Kg8 3. Rd7 Rc6
{ And now we have reached'Philidor's Position'. The game was eventually drawn. }
