{ Tragicomedies: Ljubojevic – Gligoric, Belgrade m  (9)  1979 } 1. g7
{ Milic and Bozic annotated this endgame for Chess Informant 27. In their opinion, White could have won after  1.c4+  Rg3+  2.Kc2  . But they are obviously wrong:  2...Kd6  3.g7  Ke6  or  3...Ke7  leads to a drawn pawn endgame, while after @@StartFEN@@6R1/8/2k3P1/2p5/2P5/1K4r1/8/8 w - - 0 2@@EndFEN@@  2.Ka4  Kb6  3.g7  Kb7  4.Kb5  Rg5  5.Ka4  Rg3!  , White’s king cannot break loose. }
1... Kb7
{ 1...c4+!  2.Kb4  Kb7  3.Kb5  Ka7  led to a draw. White’s king cannot stop both the rook and the king at the same time. After  4.Kc6  , the rook is released from the burden of protecting the pawn. }
2. c4 Rg2 3. Kc3
{ Black resigned. The white king goes through the center to the c5-pawn and wins it by means of zugzwang. }
