{ V.Kantorovich 1989/J.Steckner 2003, et al  (continued)   Now Steckner showed the simplest way to save the ending: }
6... f5 7. Rg8 { 7.Rb8  Rxf2  8.Rb4+  Kg3  9.Kb7  Ra2= } 7... Kf3
{ Taking the f2-pawn immediately on this or the previous move was also good enough to draw. }
8. Rg5
{ Or  8.Rb8  Rxf2  9.Rb5  Re2!   But not  9...Kg4?  10.Kb6  +-  10.Rxf5+  Kg4  , and if @@StartFEN@@8/K7/P7/1R3p1p/7P/5k2/4r3/8 w - - 2 10@@EndFEN@@  10.Kb6  Re6+  11.Ka5  Re7!= }
8... f4 9. Rxh5 Kxf2 { Draw. } *

