{ Hollis – Flórián, ol cr 1972  (continued)     a.  5.Kc2?  @@StartSquare@@Ed. b.  5.Rc7!  →Diagram 9-198@@EndSquare@@ }
1. Kc2 { The threat is  5...--  6.Rxf7+  Kxf7  7.b7  . } 1... Re3
{ The only way to survive. After bringing the rook to the eighth rank, Black will not be afraid of any interference along the b-file, and his king can advance quickly. All other plans lead to a loss.   The game in question continued as follows:  5...Rf5?  6.Rc7  Rb5  7.b7  Ke6  8.Kc3  f6  9.Kc4  Rb1  10.Kc5  Kf5  11.Rd7!  Rc1+   11...Kg4  12.Rd4+  and 13.Rb4 +-  12.Kd6  Rb1  13.Kc7  Rc1+  14.Kd8  Rb1  15.Kc8  Kg4  16.Rd6  g5  17.Rxf6  gxh4  18.gxh4  Kxh4  19.Rg6!  Kh3  20.Kc7  Black resigned in view of  20...Rxb7+   20...h4  21.Rb6  21.Kxb7  h4  22.Kc6  Kh2  23.Kd5  h3  24.Ke4  Kh1  25.Kf3  +-   Ed. note:  5...Rxg3  is analyzed in the next variation → Diagram 9-196. }
*

