{ Urkedal − Onischuk, WchT 2017  (continued)   With the king moving up to the sixth rank and the h4-pawn a target, White can no longer try to win. }
8. Rb6 Ra2+
{ @@StartSquare@@Ed. Also possible is  8...Rxa5  9.Rxg6  Kf7  with the idea that  10.Rh6  Kg7  11.Rxh5  Ra6!  locks up the rook and leads to a position we are already familiar with.@@EndSquare@@ }
9. Kg3 Ra3+ 10. Kg2 Ra2+ 11. Kg3 { Draw. } *

