{ Tragicomedies: Heinemann − Zelbel, German Bundesliga 2014 } 1... g6
{ Slightly passive and the source of Black’s problems.  1...h5  2.Kg2  Kh7  3.Kf3  f6  4.Ke3  g5=  is much easier. }
2. g4 { White holds back Black’s h- and f-pawns in typical style. } 2... Kg7 3.
Kg2 Ra1 4. a4 Ra3 5. g5
{ In the next section, we will see a position where White keeps the pawns on g4 and h4 and improves the king position first. We shall see that Black needs to play ... h5 anyway. On the other hand, if  5.h5  gxh5  , then  6.gxh5  f5!  7.f4  Ra2+!  8.Kg3  Ra3+  9.Kf2  Rh3!  is a draw. }
5... h5 6. Ra7 Kg8 7. a5 Ra4 8. Kg3 Rg4+ 9. Kh3
