Rc4 30. Kb5 Rc1 31. Kb4 Rc2 32. Kb3 Rc1 33. Kb2 Rc5 34. Qd8 Rc6 35. Qd7 Rc4 36.
Qb5 Rc8
{ Black’s only hope is to cut off the king on the c-file, but he does not have enough squares. }
37. Qa6 Rc5 38. Qf6+ Kg8 39. Qd8+ Kh7 { 39...Kg7  40.Qd4+! } 40. Qe7
{ And Black is forced to let the white king cross the c-file and eventually reach f8, winning. }
