[Result "*"]
[FEN "k7/6p1/7p/p5rP/6P1/6K1/8/R7 w - - 0 4"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ I.Rabinovich − Ragozin, USSR ch, Tbilisi 1937  (continued) } 4. Kf3 Ka7 5.
Ra4 Kb6 6. Ke3 Rd5
{ It is important to cut the king off from the queenside. After  6...Kb5?!  7.Rd4  Kc6  , winning would have been more complicated. }
7. Rf4
{ If  7.Ke4  , then  7...Rb5!  @@StartBracket@@∆ 8...Rb4+@@EndBracket@@  8.Ra1  Rg5  @@StartBracket@@driving the king back@@EndBracket@@  9.Kf4  Kb5  . Defense by frontal attack is useless here. }
7... Rd7 { ∆  8.--  Kb5  . } 8. Rf5 a4 9. g5 hxg5 10. Rxg5 a3 11. Ke4 a2 12.
Rg1 Kb5 13. Ra1 Ra7 14. Kd3
{ On  14.Kf5  , the simplest reply is  14...Ra6!  , but  14...Kb4  15.Kg6  Kb3  16.Rg1  Rc7!  is also strong enough @@StartBracket@@as inTaimanov-Averbakh, Diagram 9-110@@EndBracket@@. }
14... Kb4 15. Kc2 Ka3 16. Rg1 Rc7+ 17. Kd3 Kb2 { White resigned. } *

