{ Tragicomedies: Ilivitsky − Taimanov, USSR ch, Moscow 1955  (continued) } 8.
f4 gxf4 9. Rxf4 { ∆ 10.g5 } 9... Kg6 { Diagram 9-231 } 10. Rf5
{ In the game, White played the passive  10.Rf2?  and resigned, realizing that his position is hopeless after  10...Rxh3  . Meanwhile he could hold after the text move. }
10... Rxa2 { He has no time for capturing the h-pawn. } 11. Kg1
{ White can employ theVancura idea @@StartBracket@@see Diagram 9-43@@EndBracket@@.   11.Rh5?!  a4  12.Rxh4?  a3  13.Rh8  Rb2  -+ }
11... a4 12. Rf4
{ Even if Black’s king manages to leave the kingside by means of zugzwang: }
12... Ra3 13. Kh2 Kg7 { 13...Kf7  14.g5 } 14. Rb4
{ 14.Kg2?  Rg3+  and 15...a3. } 14... Kf7 15. Re4 Kf8 16. Rf4 Ke7
{ No more progress can be made: the king has no refuge from checks from the side near the passed pawn, therefore the rook cannot abandon the a-file. }
