{ Tragicomedies: Bogatyrchuk − Mazel, USSR ch, Moscow 1931 } 1. Rxh7
{ A grave positional error that allows the white king to be driven to the back rank.   After  1.Rh4+!  Kd3  2.Rxh7  , the draw is obvious.  2...Rc2+  can be met with  3.Kf3  . }
1... Rc2+ 2. Ke1 Rxa2 3. Re7+ Kd3 4. Rd7+ Kc2 5. Rd5
{ The decisive error. It is still not too late for the king to walk free with  5.Ke2!  , and Black cannot win. }
5... c3 6. Rxf5 Kb1 7. Rf1 Rh2 { White resigned. } *

