{ 9/28. Obukhov-Ibragimov, USSR 1991 } 1. Rb1
{ White's passivity,  1.Rh1?  caused a quick loss:  1...h3  2.Rh2  a6  ⨀  3.Kg4  Kf6  4.Rxh3  Rxh3  5.Kxh3  d5!  White resigned. And if @@StartFEN@@7r/5k2/p2p4/2p2K2/2P2P2/P6p/7R/8 w - - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Kg5  Rg8+  4.Kf5  Rg3  -+ His only correct plan was to activate the rook! }
1... h3 2. Rb7+ Kf8
{ Diagram 16-90   White had undoubtedly considered this line, but failed to discover how it should have been continued. In fact,  3.Rb8+?  fails to  3...Kg7  4.Rb7+  Kh6  -+ And @@StartFEN@@5k1r/pR6/3p4/2p2K2/2P2P2/P6p/8/8 w - - 2 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Kf6?  to  3...Rh6+  4.Kg5  h2  -+   If  3.Kg6?  then  3...Rh4!  decides:  4.f5  h2  5.f6  Rg4+  or  5...Rh6+  . And in case of  5.Rb8+  Ke7  6.f6+  Kd7  7.f7  h1=Q  -+ But one more possibility exists. }
3. Kg5 h2 { 3...Rg8+??  4.Kf6  +- } 4. Rb8+ Kg7 5. Rb7+
{ With perpetual check. } *

