{ Tragicomedies: Timoshchenko − K. Grigorian, USSR ch  (1)  , Frunze 1979  One single move was actually made in the game: }
1... Ke3
{ However, one can easily improve this line for White. After the capture on f5, it is enough to win if the black king is temporarily cut off from the approach to the lower half of the board: @@StartFEN@@r7/P7/5p2/R2K1k2/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4.Ra4!  (instead of 4.Kc6+?)  Kg5  5.Kc6  f5  6.Kb7  Re8  7.a8=Q  Rxa8  8.Rxa8  +- }
2. Ra4
{ Black resigned. Now when his king is cut off from the f5-pawn, he will be inevitably put into zugzwang. }
2... Kf3 3. Kd3 Kg3 4. Ke3 { Zugzwang. } 4... Re8+ { 4...Kh3  5.Kf3  ⨀ } 5. Kd4
Ra8 6. Kc5 { White wins. } *

