{ Rook versus Knight    The Lone Knight   In the chapter, 'Rook vs. Pawns'  (the portion devoted to 'Promoting the Pawn to a Knight')  , we were introduced to the most important knight-versus-rook positions for the practical player. Let's revisit the basic conclusions:    Usually, a knight draws easily against a rook. But there are exceptions:    When the knight becomes separated from the king, then it can sometimes be trapped;    When the knight is in the corner, it will be lost through zugzwang }
1. -- *

