{ There are times when a lone knight can hold even against rook and pawn – and not just in those cases where the pawn may be attacked and captured. It can be enough just to prevent the enemy king from reaching its pawn.  Em. Lasker – Ed.Lasker, New York 1924 }
1. Na4 Re3 2. Nb2 Ke4 3. Na4 Kf3
{ Black can only improve his position if he can get his king over to the pawn. And the only way to get there is by bringing it around the rook. White must take measures against ...Ke2-d2-c2 -+ }
4. Ka3
