{ Multi-Pawn Endgames    Pawns on One Side of the Board     When there are three pawns against three, or even two pawns against two pawns, all on the same side of the board, the rook will, in the overwhelming majority of cases, win against the knight. But if the weaker side has an extra pawn, then he has real chances to draw. }
