{ Vidmar − Alekhine, San Remo 1930  (analysis)   There is another method of defense. If we leave the king at h2 and the knight at e4, the incursion of the black king is not dangerous; it will be driven off the f1- and f2-squares by checks at g3 and e4. This plan was successfully employed in the game Kuzmin-Miles  (Bath, ech tt 1973)  , in which the same position arose, but with the black rook at a4. }
12. Nh5 Ra6 13. Kh2 Kf2 14. Ng3 Re6
{ 14...Rg6  15.Ne4+  Kf1  16.Ng3+  Kf2  17.Ne4+  Ke3  18.Ng3= } 15. Ne4+ Ke3
16. Kg3 Rg6+ 17. Kh2 Kf4 18. Nf2 Rd6 19. Ne4 Rd5 20. Ng3 Ra5 21. Kh3 g6 22.
Ne2+ Ke3 23. Ng3 Kf4 24. Ne2+ Ke3 { Draw. } *

