9... Kd4 10. Nf4 Ke3 11. Ne6
{ Also hopeless are  11.Nh3  Ra2  12.Nf4  Ra5  13.Ne6  Re5  , and @@StartFEN@@8/6p1/7p/7P/5N2/4kPK1/3r2P1/8 w - - 7 11@@EndFEN@@  11.Kg4  Rd4  12.g3  Ra4  13.Kf5  Kxf3  . But not Fine’s suggestion  13...Ra5+?  14.Kg6  Rg5+  in view of  15.Kh7!  Kxf3  16.Ne6  Rxh5  17.Nxg7  , with a drawn position.   Ed. note: continued in the next variation → Diagram 10-24 }
