[Black "When the Knight Is Stronger than the Rook"]
[Result "*"]

{ When the Knight is Stronger than the Rook   The knight is no weaker, and sometimes even stronger, than the rook when the board is strewn with pawn chains and the rook has nowhere to break into the enemy camp.  Another possibility: sometimes, the rook has a hard time dealing with a far-advanced enemy passed pawn supported by the knight. In such situations, the knight's tactical abilities come to the fore. It can create forks, win tempi by checking the enemy king, or cut the rook off from the pawn. }
