{ Tragicomedies: Euwe − Hromdka, Pistyan 1922 } 1... h4
{ Black could have won quite easily:  1...Kh3!  2.Bd4  Rg2+  3.Kh1  Rd2  etc. And if @@StartFEN@@8/8/8/7p/3B4/7k/6r1/6K1 w - - 3 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Kf1  Kg3!  4.Be5+  Kf3  5.Bf6  Rg4  . }
2. Bd4 Kh3
{ Now the bishop comes to  the h2-b8 diagonal, and the position becomes drawn.   A win, although rather complicated, was still possible:  2...Re2!  3.Ba7  Rb2  or  3...Re8  4.Bb6  Re7  5.Bc5  Rd7  The rook gradually deprives the bishop of important squares prior to decisive action on the kingside. }
3. Be5 Rg2+ 4. Kf1 { Draw. } *

