{ 11/4. Y. Roslov, 1996 } 1. f7+
{ If  1.Kf2?  Bd5  2.Ke3  Kf7  3.Kd4  Bb3  , the game arrives at the del Rio position. To avoid this, only tactical measures will do. }
1... Ke7 2. Rd6 { Rather than  2.Rh8?  Ba6+!  3.Kf2  Kxf7  . } 2... Bh1
{ Amazingly enough, the bishop cannot find refuge from rook attacks:  2...Kf8  3.Rd8+  Kxf7  4.Rd7+  and if  2...Bc8  3.f8=Q+  Kxf8  4.Rd8+  , while after  2...Bf3  3.f8=Q+  or  3.Rf6  . }
3. Kg1 Be4 { 3...Bb7  4.Rd7+! } 4. Re6+ { White wins. } *

