{ Kasparov – Yusupov, Linares 1993  (analysis)   The logic of the previous example can be applied here: the correct plan is to play for zugzwang rather than driving the king off. }
1. Rd8 Kc7 2. Rd4 Kb7 3. Rd7+ Kc8 4. Kc6 Bc2 5. Rd4 Bb3 { 5...Kb8  6.Kb6  +- }
6. Kb6 { Ed. note: the game continuation → Diagram 11-35 } *

