{ Tragicomedies: Bellón – Tatai, Rome 1977    Recalling theKasparov-Yusupov endgame, we can find the solution easily:  1...Rc7!  or  1...Rc6!  2.Bb6   2.Bb8  Rc5  and if @@StartFEN@@8/B7/p1r5/P7/8/1k6/8/1K6 w - - 1 2@@EndFEN@@  2.Be3  Re6  3.Bd2  Rf6  -+  2...Rd6  3.Kc1  Rd5!  ⨀ -+ }
1... Rh2
{ In Chess Informant 25, Milic awarded this move an exclamation mark. } 2. Kc1
Kc3
{ It was still not too late to return to the correct plan,  2...Rh5!  3.Bb6  Rd5! }
3. Kd1 Rd2+ 4. Ke1 Kd3 5. Bb6 Rh2 6. Bd8 Rh1+ 7. Kf2 Rh8 8. Bb6 Re8 9. Kf1 Kd2
