{ Tragicomedies: Bellón − Tatai, Rome 1977  (continued) } 10. Bc5
{ A mistake in return, unnoticed by both Chess Informant and Encyclopedia of Chess Endings. The correct defensive method, as demonstrated by Yusupov against Kasparov, was  10.Kf2!  or  10.Kg2!  Rf8  11.Kg3  Kc3  12.Kg4  Kb4  13.Kg5!   Or  13.Bc7!  – it is important not to let the rook to  f5  .  13...Rf1  14.Kg4  Ra1  15.Kf3  Rxa5  16.Bxa5+  Kxa5  17.Ke2= }
10... Re5 11. Bb4+
{ Or  11.Bb6  Rf5+!  12.Kg2  Kc3  13.Kg3  Kb4  14.Kg4  Rxa5  -+ } 11... Kd3 12.
Kf2 Rb5 13. Be1 Rf5+ { 13...Rb1!  , winning the bishop. } 14. Kg3 Ke2 15. Kg4
{ 15.Bb4  Rb5  16.Bc3  Rb3  -+ } 15... Rc5 { White resigned. } *

