[SetUp "1"]

{ Diagram 11-38  (analysis) } 1... Bd4 2. Rb4
{ With tempo, and this fact turns out to be decisive. } 2... Bc3 3. Rc4 Bb2
{ 3...Be1  4.Kf6  Kh7  5.Rc6!  Bxg3  6.Kg5  +- } 4. g4 hxg4 5. Rxg4 Kh7
{ 5...Kg7  6.h5  +- } 6. Kf7 Kh6 7. Rxg6+ Kh5 8. Rg2 Bc3 9. Rh2
{ Diagram 11-39 } 9... Bd4 { 9...Be1  10.Kf6  Bxh4+  11.Kf5  ⨀ } 10. Ke6 Bg1
11. Rh1 Bf2 12. Kf5
{ We come to a theoretical position that is won for White, although the proof is very complicated: the main line lasts some twenty moves! }
