[SetUp "1"]

{ Khalifman − Leko, Budapest m  (3)  , 2000  (analysis)     @@StartSquare@@In the game,  2.Kf4  was played@@EndSquare@@, however the most direct way to a victory starts with the text move. }
2. Rd8+ Kf7 3. Rb8
{ Diagram 11-42   a.  3...h5  4.Rb7+  Kg8  5.Rxg7+!  Kxg7  6.Ke4  Kf7  7.Kd5  +-   b.  3...h6  4.Rb7+  Kg8  5.Ke4   5.Rxg7+?  Kxg7  6.Ke4  is premature in view of  6...Kf7  7.Kd5  Ke7!  8.Ke5  h5=  or  8.gxh6  Kf7=  5...hxg5  6.Rxg7+!  Kxg7  7.hxg5  Kf7  8.Kd5  +-   c.  3...Bc3  4.Rb7+  Kg8  5.Kg4  ∆ 6.h5 +-   d.   3...Ke7  4.h5!  gxh5  5.Rb6  Kf7  6.Kg3  ∆ Kh4xh5 +-  e. @@StartSquare@@Ed. see the text move@@EndSquare@@ }
3... Bf8 4. Rb7+
{ 4.h5?  gxh5  5.Rb6  fails on account of  5...Kg8!  6.Kg3  h6!  7.gxh6  Kh7  8.Kh4  Bxh6  9.Kxh5  Bd2= }
4... Kg8 5. Kg4 { ∆ 6.h5 +- } 5... h5+ 6. Kf3
{ Rather than  6.Kf4?  Bd6+  7.Ke4  Bg3  . Black could have held this position if he had been able to bring the bishop to the a1-h8 diagonal, but all the roads to it are cut off. }
6... Bg7
{ 6...Bc5  7.Ke4  Bf2  8.Ke5  Bxh4  9.Kf6  +- Or  6...Bd6  7.Rb6  and in case of @@StartFEN@@5bk1/1R6/6p1/6Pp/7P/5K2/8/8 b - - 1 6@@EndFEN@@  6...Ba3  7.Ke4  ∆ Ke5-f6. }
7. Rxg7+ { White wins. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
