[SetUp "1"]

{ Khalifman − Leko, Budapest m  (3)  , 2000  (continued) } 10... Bh4
{ 10...Be3  is simpler; if  11.Rh7  Bd2  12.g7  , then  12...Bc3  or  12...Bg5  . }
11. Rh7 Bg5 12. g7 h5
{ A study-like salvation!   All other moves lose:  12...Bd8?  13.Rh8+  , while after  12...Bh4?  13.Rxh6  and  12...Be3?  13.Kf6  , while after @@StartFEN@@6k1/6PR/4K2p/6b1/8/8/8/8 b - - 0 12@@EndFEN@@  12...Kxh7?  13.Kf7  +- }
13. Rxh5 Bf6
{ The bishop is taboo in view of stalemate. The g7-pawn will be lost, and White cannot reach the basic winning position with the king in the dangerous corner. }
14. Rh3 Bxg7 15. Ke7 Bb2 16. Rb3 Bd4 17. Rd3 Bb2 18. Rg3+ Kh7 19. Ke6 Kh6 20.
Kf5 Kh7 21. Rg6 Bc3 22. Kg5 Bb2 23. Kh5 Bc3 24. Rg2 Bd4 25. Rd2 Bc3 26. Rc2 Ba1
27. Rc7+ Kg8 28. Rd7 { Draw. } *

