{ Even if White succeeds in preventing a fortress such as inDiagram 11-29 by playing g2-g4 at the proper moment, Black still can hold if he builds another elementary fortress.  Olafsson – Larsen, Las Palmas 1974  This barrier is also not to be breached. }
1... Bg5 2. Ra5 Bh4 { But surely not  2...Kg7?  3.Rxg5  hxg5  4.Ke7  +- } 3.
Ra1 Bg5 4. Ra4 { 4.Rh1  Bh4!= } 4... Kg7 5. Ra7+ Kg8 6. Rf7 Kh8 7. Ke5
{ 7.Rf6  Kg7= } 7... Kg8 { And the game ended in a draw. } *

