{ Would the evaluation of the position be changed with the white pawn on h2 instead of h3? In such cases, White has the following way to play for a win: the king comes to h3 and drives the bishop away from h4, then Kg3 and h2-h4-h5 follow. I have seen analysis of this situation only in a two-volume endgame treatise by Villeneuve @@StartBracket@@in French, 1984@@EndBracket@@. }
