{ Radev − Pribyl, Tbilisi 1971  (analysis) } 1. Rd7+
{ The alternative to 8.Kg5.   For example  8...Ke8  9.Rh7  g3  10.Rxh5  Bc1  11.Kf6!   Rather than  11.Rh7?  in view of the pretty response  11...Bg5!!=  11...Kd7   11...g2  12.Rh8+  Kd7  13.Rg8  and @@StartFEN@@4k3/8/5K2/7R/7P/6p1/8/2b5 b - - 2 4@@EndFEN@@  11...Bb2+  12.Ke6  12.Rd5+  Kc6  13.Rd8  ∆ 14.Rg8. And if  12...Ke8  13.Re5+  Kd7   13...Kf8  14.Rc5  Bb2+  15.Kg6  14.Re4  and 15.Rg4+- Black can also try: }
1... Kf8 { White should play: } 2. Kg6 g3 3. Rd5 { 10.Rf7+!? } 3... Bc1 4. Rd8+
{ An important intermediate check that prevents the bishop from accessing e3 in the future.   Kholmov analyzed solely  11.Rd3  but after  11...Bf4  White has neither  12.Rf3?  g2  13.Rxf4+  Kg8=  nor  12.Rd1?  Be3=  @@StartBracket@@However, @@StartFEN@@5k2/8/6K1/7p/5b1P/3R2p1/8/8 w - - 4 5@@EndFEN@@  12.Rd8+  Ke7  13.Rd1  is still playable@@EndBracket@@. }
4... Ke7 5. Rd1 Ba3 { 12...Bf4!?  but  12...Be3??  13.Re1 } 6. Rg1
{ 13.Kxh5?  Bc5= } 6... Bd6 7. Kxh5 Kf6 8. Kg4
{ This position can be achieved much more rapidly after 8.Kg5 @@StartSquare@@Ed. as seen previously → Diagram 11-52@@EndSquare@@. }
