{ Winning Tactical Tricks   The queen is the strongest piece; therefore  playing for mate  occurs in queen endgames more often than in other kinds of endings. Among other techniques,  winning the queen   (usually by means of a skewer check)  and  exchange of queens  should be mentioned. These three tools can all be seen in the next example.  K.Eucken 1947 }
1. c4
{ Every capture of the pawn leads to a mate in one. After the text move, White forces an exchange of the queens. }
1... Qd3
{ 1...Qe4  has the same consequences after  2.Qf5+!  Qxf5  3.gxf5  +- Finally, every other retreat of the queen leads to its loss, for example:  a.  1...Qa8  2.Qe5+  Kxc4  3.Qc3+  Kd5  4.Qf3+   b.  1...Qh1  2.Qe5+  Kxc4  3.Qc3+  Kd5  4.Qc6+   c.  1...Qg8  2.Qe5+  Kxc4  3.Qc3+  Kd5  4.Qb3+ }
2. Qc6+ Kd4 3. Qd5+ Ke3 4. Qxd3+ Kxd3 5. cxb5 { White wins. } *

