{ Tragicomedies: Batuev − Simagin, Riga 1954    As we know, defending against a central pawn is practically always a hopeless matter. The simplest winning process here is  1...Qb4+  2.Kc2  Qc4+  3.Kb2  Kd2  @@StartBracket@@king-to-king!@@EndBracket@@. But miracles happen from time to time. }
1... e2 2. Qg1+ Kd2 3. Qc1+ Kd3 4. Qc3#
{ A year later, Simagin got a gift in return. @@StartSquare@@Ed. see the next variation@@EndSquare@@ }
*

