{ 12/3. L. van Vliet, 1888 } 1. Qb4 { Zugzwang. } 1... Qh1
{ 1...Qd5  2.Qa4+  Kb6  3.Qb3+!  Qxb3  4.b8=Q+    1...Qf3  2.Qa4+  Kb6  3.Qb3+!    1...Qg2  2.Qa3+  Kb6  3.Qb2+! }
2. Qa3+ Kb6 { Or  2...Kb5  3.Qb2+  Kc4  4.Ka7  +- } 3. Qb2+ Kc7
{ If  3...Kc5  then  4.Ka7  Qh7  5.Qb6+  and 6.Ka6 +-. In case of @@StartFEN@@K7/1P6/1k6/8/8/8/1Q6/7q b - - 5 3@@EndFEN@@  3...Ka6  the following familiar tactical device decides:  4.Qa2+  Kb6  5.Qb1+!  When the black king is on c7, the same idea of winning the queen works diagonally. }
4. Qh2+ Qxh2 5. b8=Q+ { White wins. } *

