{ 12/5. L. Kubbel, 1929 } 1. Qg2
{ ∆ 2.Qg4#   Both  1.Qg1?  Ke4  and @@StartFEN@@8/2p2p2/4p3/q1p1p3/5k1K/1P6/3P4/7Q w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.Qf1+?  Ke4  2.Qc4+  Kf3  3.Qd3+  @@StartBracket@@and now not  3...Kf2?  4.Qe3+  Kf1  5.Kg3  +-@@EndBracket@@, but  3...Kf4!  4.Qe2  e4  give nothing. }
1... f5 { 1...e4  is quite bad:  2.Qg3+  Kf5  3.Qg5# } 2. Qe2
{ ∆ 3.Qe3#   Rather than  2.Qf1+?  Ke4  3.Qc4+  Kf3  4.Qd3+  , here  4...Kf4?  is obviously wrong  5.Qe3#  , therefore  4...Kf2!  5.Qe3+  Kf1  and  6.Kg3??  loses to  6...f4+  . }
2... e4 3. Qe1 { ∆ 4.Qg3# } 3... Ke5 4. d4+
{ And 5.Qxa5. Chasing after the king has suddenly resulted in catching the queen. }
