{ J. Speelman  This is a standard configuration of a perpetual check, when the king cannot abandon its queen. }
1... Qa1+ 2. Kd3 Qd1+ 3. Ke3 Qg1+ 4. Ke4 Qg4+ 5. Kd5 Qd7+ 6. Kc5 Qa7+ 7. Kc4
Qa4+ 8. Kc3 Qa1+
{ etc. This is sometimes called a “wheel check” because it rotates like a wheel. }
