{ Tragicomedies: Alekhine – Maróczy, New York 1924    White’s extra pawn must bring him a relatively easy win. Alekhine recommends  1.Qd4!  Qc2+  2.Kg3  @@StartBracket@@ ∆  2...--  3.Qxd5  Qxb2  4.Qd8+  Kg7  5.Qd4+  @@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@6k1/1p3p1p/6p1/3p4/3Q4/P3PPKP/1Pq3P1/8 b - - 3 2@@EndFEN@@  2...Qc6  3.a4  .   And  1.Kg3!  , planning 2.Kh2, was also strong. However, White greedily went after the b7-pawn. }
1. Qc8+ Kg7 2. Qxb7 { It was not too late to retreat:  2.Qc3+  . } 2... Qd2+ 3.
Kg3 d4 4. exd4 Qg5+ { Draw. The king cannot escape the checks. } *

