{ Tragicomedies: Shcherbakov − Arlazarov, USSR 1972 } 1. f6
{ The game Mackenzie-Sergeant @@StartBracket@@Edinburgh 1920@@EndBracket@@, where the same position occurred, continued  1.Kg6?  Qxg4+  2.Kf7  @@StartBracket@@here  2...Kh7!=  should have been played@@EndBracket@@  2...Qh5+??  3.Kf8  and Black resigned because of an inevitable mate. But @@StartFEN@@7k/6p1/4Q2p/5P1K/5qPP/8/8/8 w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.g5  hxg5  2.Kg6  Qb8  3.hxg5  (V. Keymer)  wins as well. }
1... Kh7 { 1...gxf6  2.Kg6  +- } 2. fxg7
{ White overlooks a queen sacrifice that forces a stalemate.   Both  2.Qf5+!  Qxf5+  3.gxf5  gxf6  4.Kg4  Kg7  5.Kf4  Kf7  6.Ke4  Ke7  7.Kd5  Kd7  8.h5  ⨀ and a more spectacular @@StartFEN@@8/6pk/4QP1p/7K/5qPP/8/8/8 w - - 1 2@@EndFEN@@  2.f7!  Qe5+!  @@StartBracket@@of course not  3.Qxe5??  g6#  @@EndBracket@@ but  3.g5!  Qxe6  4.f8=N+!  were winning. }
2... Qf7+ { Draw. } *

