{ Marshall − Maróczy, Ostende 1905  (continued) } 9. g3
{ Diagram 12-38   9.b4?  axb4  10.axb4  Qe4  is hopeless. } 9... a4
{ Maróczy fixes the queenside pawns while the white queen still occupies a miserable position.  9...g5?  would have been less precise in view of  10.b4  a4  11.Qe1  with drawing chances. }
10. f4 { 10.h3  is more tenacious. } 10... Kg8
{ Zugzwang! If  11.Kh1  , then  11...Qf2  and  ...h6-h5-h4. } 11. h3 h5 12. h4
Kg7 { Zugzwang again. } 13. Kh1
{ 13.Kf1  loses right away to  13...Qh2  . If @@StartFEN@@8/5pk1/4p1p1/1p2P2p/p4P1P/P5P1/1Pq5/Q5K1 w - - 1 13@@EndFEN@@  13.Qa2  , then  13...Qd1+  14.Kf2  Kf8  , and the white queen is arrested. }
13... Qf2 14. Qg1 Qxb2
{ Ed. note: continued in the next variation → Diagram 12-39 } *

