{ Marshall − Maróczy, Ostende 1905  (continued) } 15. Qc5
{ Diagram 12-39  White lunges in a desperate counterattack but his hopes for perpetual check are not realized. }
15... b4 16. f5
{ After  16.Qe7  bxa3?!  17.Qf6+  Kg8  18.Qd8+  Kh7  19.Qe7  Qb1+  20.Kh2  Qf5  21.Qxa3  , White still could have had some hopes. However, Black plays  16...b3!  17.Qf6+  Kg8  18.Qd8+  Kh7  19.Qe7  Qb1+  20.Kh2  Qf5  21.Qb7  Kg7  with an easy win. }
16... exf5 17. e6 bxa3 18. exf7
{ 18.e7  a2  19.e8=N+  Kg8  or  19...Kh7  makes no sense. } 18... Kxf7
{ The black king easily escapes from the checks in White’s territory. } 19.
Qc7+ Ke6 20. Qc6+ Ke5 21. Qxa4 a2 22. Qe8+ Kd5 23. Qd7+ Ke4 24. Qc6+ Ke3 25.
Qc5+ Qd4 26. Qa3+ Qd3
