{ 12/10. Adorján-Orsó, Hungary ch, Budapest 1977  White has an active queen and generates a mating attack. }
1. f5 exf5 { 1...Qxg4  2.Qxf7+  Ka6  3.Qxe6  is also winning for White. } 2.
Qe7+ Ka6 { Or  2...Kc6  3.Qe8+  Kc7  4.gxh5!  Qxh5  5.e6  +- } 3. b4 cxb4 4.
axb4 b5 { Diagram 16-99 The only defense against mate. } 5. e6
{ In the game, White went astray with  5.Qd6+?  Kb7!  , and there was no win. The remainder of the game was  6.Qd7+  Kb8  7.Qxb5+  Kc8  8.Qe8+  Kc7  9.Qe7+  Kc8  10.g5  f4  11.Qe8+  Kc7  12.Qe7+  Kc8  13.Qc5+  Kb7  14.Qd5+  Kb8  15.Ka3  Qxg5  16.Qd6+  Kc8  , Draw agreed. }
5... Qxg4
{ 5...fxe6  6.Qd7!  and if  5...Qxe6  6.Qxe6+  fxe6  7.gxh5  f4  8.h6  f3  9.h7  f2  10.h8=Q  f1=Q  11.Qc8+  Kb6  12.c5# }
6. Qd6+ { 6.cxb5+  Kb6  7.Qc5+  Kb7  8.Qd5+  Kb8  9.exf7  is equivalent. } 6...
Kb7 7. Qd7+ Kb8 { Otherwise he will be mated. } 8. Qxb5+ Kc7 9. Qd7+ Kb8 10.
Qd8+ Kb7 11. Qd5+ Kc7 12. exf7 { White wins. } *

