{ A Solitary Rook   The side that has a rook will try, except in very rare cases, to build a fortress. We shall study the most important theoretical positions here, both drawn and winning. Sometimes one must play dozens of precise moves in a row in order to destroy the opponent's line of defense.  However, the winning plans that we should know are mostly standard, even when they are quite complicated tactically. Master Khenkin has greatly contributed to the theory of this sort of endgame; he wrote the corresponding section for Averbakh's endgame treatise and, for this purpose, analyzed a huge number of new positions. }
1. -- *

