{ 13/1. L. Prokeš, 1938 } 1. Rd8
{ 1.Rh8?  loses after  1...Qa3+  2.Kb7  Qb2+  3.Ka7  Qb6+!   But surely not  3...Qxh8?  4.c8=Q+  Qxc8  stalemate.  4.Ka8  Qxc7  5.Rh5+  Kc4  6.Rh4+  Kc3  7.Rh3+  Kc2  and checks are exhausted. }
1... Qh6+ 2. Kb7 Qb6+ 3. Ka8 Qxc7 4. Rd5+ Kb6
{ The king can be forced to go to the sixth rank only when the white rook is on the d-file. There is no use in  4...Kc4  5.Rd4+  etc. }
5. Rb5+ { 5.Rd6+  is also good. } 5... Ka6 6. Rb6+
{ With stalemate or perpetual check. } *

