{ 8.Kf1!  is equivalent. But  8.Rd1?  Ke7  9.Re1+  Kf7  10.Re8  is premature in view of   10.g3  Qd6!  10...Qf4!  11.d8=Q   11.Re1  Qd2  and if @@StartFEN@@4R3/3P1kp1/2P4p/5p2/5q2/8/5PP1/6K1 w - - 6 4@@EndFEN@@  11.g3  Qc1+  12.Kh2  Qf1  11...Qc1+  12.Kh2  Qf4+  , while after  12.Re1  Qxe1+  13.Kh2  Qxf2  and White cannot escape from checks @@StartBracket@@Dvoretsky@@EndBracket@@. }
1... f4 2. Rd1 Ke7 { 9...Qd8  10.c7  +- } 3. Re1+ Kf7 4. Re8 Qxc6 5. d8=N+
{ Black resigned. } *

