{ Now we come to the most important class of positions: the king protects the pawn while the rook tries to keep hostile pieces away from it.   The Pawn on the Seventh Rank   Philidor, 1777 }
1. Qh8 Rc6
{ Black holds his king on the seventh and eighth ranks, preventing the white queen from entering the important d8-square. The rook has two protected squares at its disposal @@StartBracket@@e6 and c6@@EndBracket@@; therefore a zugzwang cannot be created. }
