{ Philidor, 1777  (continued) } 1... Re4
{ 14...Ke4  15.Qc4+  Kf5  16.Qd3+  Ke6  17.Ke8  +- Or @@StartFEN@@5K2/8/3p4/3kr3/8/2Q5/8/8 b - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  14...Re6  15.Qb3+  Ke5  16.Kf7  Rf6+  17.Ke7  +- }
2. Qd3+ Rd4
{ Or  15...Ke5  16.Ke7  d5  17.Qg3+  Rf4  18.Qe3+  Re4  19.Qg5+  Kd4+  20.Kd6  . And if  17...Kd4+  18.Kd6  Kc4  19.Qg2  Rd4  20.Qc2+  , or @@StartFEN@@8/4K3/8/3pk3/4r3/6Q1/8/8 b - - 1 4@@EndFEN@@  17...Kf5+  18.Kd6  d4  19.Qd3  Kf4  20.Kd5 }
3. Qf5+ Kc4 4. Qc2+ Kd5 5. Ke7 Ke5 6. Kd7 Rd5 7. Qe2+ Kf4 8. Kc6 Rd4 9. Kb5 Kf5
10. Qe3 Re4 11. Qd3 Ke5 12. Kc6 Rd4 13. Qe3+ Re4 14. Qg5+ Ke6 15. Qd5+
{ An analogous plan succeeds against a black pawn on d5. With the pawn on d4, Black also loses. If the pawn stands on c6 or c5, White wins too, although his task is even more complicated. }
