{ A Knight Pawn on the Fifth or Sixth Rank    A draw still can be achieved when a knight pawn has left the seventh rank. If it is standing on the sixth rank, Black should keep his king behind it; if the pawn has reached the fourth or fifth rank; the king may be placed in front of it as well.   B. Guretzky-Cornitz, 1864 }
1. Qf7+ Kb8 2. Qe6 Kb7 3. Qd7+ Kb8 4. Ke4 Ka8 5. Qa4+ Kb7 6. Kd4 Rc7
{ Black lets the white king go ahead in order to keep his own king behind the pawn. @@StartSquare@@Ed.  6...Ra5?  is analyzed inDiagram 13-23@@EndSquare@@ }
7. Kd5 Rc5+ 8. Kd6 Rc7
{ Ed. note: continued in the next variation → Diagram 13-22 } *

