{ Pawns on Adjacent Files   Almost all positions with the pawns on the same files are lost. Positions with the pawns on adjacent files, however, are sometimes tenable, but only if the weaker side's pawn stands on its initial square.   In the next diagram, if Black is on move he holds by means of transferring his king to g7.  F. Dedrle, 1925 }
1... Kf8 2. Kg4 Kg7 3. Kf5 Rg6 4. Qb2+ Kh7
{ White cannot do anything as  5.Qf6  leads to a drawn pawn endgame.   Ed. note: for White on move in the initial position, see → Diagram 13-32 EXTRA. }
