{ A Fortress with Multiple Pawns   From the multitude of theoretically known positions where a rook opposes a queen more or less successfully, we select several of the most important and characteristic cases.   V. Khenkin, 1962 }
1... Kh8 { Both  1...Kg7  and  1...Rf1  are not by any means worse than this. }
2. Qxg6 Rf7+ { 2...Re5+ } 3. Ke6 Re7+
{ With a draw by a stalemate or perpetual check. With a shift up, the position is still drawn. But when shifted down, it is lost: @@StartFEN@@8/8/4K2k/4Q1p1/5r1p/7P/8/8 w - - 0 0@@EndFEN@@ White wins by means of a queen attack along the last rank. }
*

