{ J.Polgar – Kasparov, Dos Hermanas 1996 } 1. Ra8
{ Why does Polgar not flee from the edge with her king?  1.Kg4!  Rf4+  2.Kh3  ∆ 3. Kg2= suggests itself. }
1... Rg1 2. Rf8+ Ke5 3. Re8+ Kf4 { The knight is taboo in view of mate. } 4.
Rf8+ Ke4 5. Re8+ Kf3 6. Kh5
{ She could try playing for a stalemate:  6.Rf8+!?  Nf4  7.Rg8!  For example,  7...Rh1+  8.Kg5  Rg1+  9.Kh4!  Ng6+  10.Kh5  Kf4!  @@StartBracket@@the only method of holding the white king on the edge@@EndBracket@@  11.Rg7  Kf5  12.Rf7+  pushing the black king somewhat away and thereby reducing the danger of a mating attack. }
6... Ng3+ { Ed. note: continued in the next variation → Diagram 14-5 } *

