2. Bc3
{ This makes White’s task more difficult. Better was  2.Bc7!  f4  3.h3  Rh2  4.Kd4  Rxh3  5.Ke4  and White is well placed. And after @@StartFEN@@8/2B4p/2B1k3/2K2pp1/8/5P2/5r1P/8 b - - 2 2@@EndFEN@@  2...Rc2+  3.Kb6  h6!?  4.h3  , and White should hold with precise defense. Instead, Miles gives away the h2-pawn, pinning his hopes on the cooperation of the bishops and the centralized king, but his wishes do not come true. }
