{ After this mistake, Black gets in ...f4+ with tempo and White’s position quickly deteriorates. White had to play  5.Kd3+!  Kg6  6.Be5!  f4  7.Be4+  Kf7  8.Bd5+  either gives perpetual check or displaces the black king. In case of @@StartFEN@@8/7p/6k1/3BBpp1/8/3K1P2/7r/8 b - - 7 6@@EndFEN@@  6...Rh1  7.Bc6  and he can probably still hold with best play. }
5... Kg6 6. Be1
{ Now if  6.Be5  f4+  7.Kd3  h5  8.Be4+  Kh6  9.Bd6  h4  and the pawn goes through. }
6... f4+ 7. Kd4 h5 8. Ke5 h4
