{ 14/1. Beliavsky-Miles, Thessaloniki ol 1984  A draw is reached by force after: }
1... c2
{ In the game, Black played  1...Rh8?!  Although the position remained drawn, the defense has become more complicated, and this eventually led to the decisive error.  2.Be4  @@StartBracket@@  2...Rh1!?  @@EndBracket@@  2...Ke1  @@StartBracket@@  3.Ke3!?  @@EndBracket@@  3.Na3  Kd1   Karsten Müller recommended  3...Kd2  4.f5  Rh4!?  or @@StartFEN@@7r/8/8/8/4BP2/N1p2K2/3k4/8 w - - 5 4@@EndFEN@@  4.Nc4+  Kd1!?  4.f5  Rh7?  5.Kf4  Rf7  6.Ke5  – White has been able to coordinate his pieces and won easily. After  4.f5  necessary was  4...Kc1  5.Kf4  Rf8  or  5...Kb2  . }
2. Ne3+ Kd2 3. Bxc2 Rc8 { And  4.--  Rc3=  is inevitable, with a draw. } *

