{ Sveshnikov – Psakhis, Erevan zt, 1982  Nevertheless, the queen is a powerful piece and can sometimes break fortresses. This endgame was considered a fortress for a long time until Karsten Müller found the win in 2019. }
1. Rxc7 Qxc7 2. Bxc7 b2 3. Kh2 b1=Q 4. Be5
{ The queen enjoys unlimited freedom of action but cannot destroy the enemy defense without the king’s support. The king cannot break through the two adjacent diagonals controlled by the bishops. Hence, the way to the queenside is closed. However, the king can walk to h5 and penetrate on the kingside with the help of g7-g5. }
4... Qd3 5. Bb8 Qe3 6. Bc7 Qe2 7. Be5 Qh5 8. Kg1 Kg6 9. Bc7 Qe2 10. Kh2
