{ Chernin – Marjanovic, Subotica izt 1987  (analysis) } 3. Rf4
{ This sharper continuation merited attention. } 3... Qb1+
{ The advance  3...a3  , as on the previous move, is still not favorable for Black.  4.Ra5  Qb1+  5.Kg2  ∆ 6.Rfa4  5...Qb7+  6.e4  Qb4  7.Ra6  ∆ Rf3. }
4. Kh2 Qb6 { 4...Qb2  is useless in view of  5.Ra5  a3  6.Kg2  +- } 5. Rxh5 Qa6
6. Rg4+ Kf8 7. Rh8+ Ke7 8. Re4+ Kd7 { Diagram 14-49 } 9. Rf8
{ Now White can bring his rook back to defend:  9.Rd4+  Ke7  10.Rd2  a3  11.Ra2  The attack against the king is, however, even stronger. }
9... a3 { 9...Kd6  10.Rxf7  +- } 10. Rxf7+ Kd8 11. Rb4 Kc8
{ 11...Qd6  12.Ra4  +- } 12. Rg4
{ With inevitable mate or win of the queen. A rather standard attack with two rooks! }
