{ Tondivar – Lutz, Leeuwarden 1994 } 1... Kg6
{ 1...b4?  2.Rxa6  b3  3.Rb6  followed with 4.c7 results in a draw, while @@StartFEN@@8/6pk/pRP4p/1p6/8/2r4P/6K1/8 b - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...Ra3  can be met, say, with  2.Rb8  , and the black rook must go back to c3. Black can win only through a king advance! }
2. Rxa6 Kh5 3. Rb6 { 3.Ra7  fails after  3...Rxc6  4.Rxg7  Rg6+ } 3... Kh4 4.
Rxb5 Rc2+ 5. Kg1 Kxh3 { Rather than  5...Rxc6?  6.Rb3= } 6. Rb7
{ 6.Rb3+  Kh4  7.Rb4+  Kh5  8.Rb6  does not help in view of  8...g5  9.Kf1  g4  followed by ...Kg5, ...h5, ...Kh4. }
6... g5 7. c7 g4 8. Rb6 h5 { White resigned. } *

