{ A. Yusupov, 1995  (continued)    From the point of view of the first plan, the situation has not changed. But the widening of the beachhead has become much more effective than in the initial position. }
1. g5 hxg5 2. Kxg5 Kf7 3. Kf4 Kf6 4. Ke4 Kf7
{ 10...e5  is impossible here in view of  11.Kd5  Kf5  12.Kd6  Kf4  13.Kc7  Kf3  14.Kxb7  Kxf2  15.Kc6  e4  16.b7  with the winning endgame @@StartBracket@@a queen versus a central pawn@@EndBracket@@. }
5. Ke5 Ke7 6. f3
{ White should preserve his second spare tempo for the future } 6... Kd7 7. Kf6
Kd6 { 13...Kc6  14.Kxe6  Kxb6  15.f4  transposes into the main line. } 8. f4
Kd7 9. Kf7 Kd6 10. Ke8
{ A routine technique: the opposition is utilized by means of an outflanking. }
10... Kc6 11. Ke7 Kxb6 { 17...Kd5  18.Kd7 } 12. Kxe6 Kc7 13. f5 Kd8 14. Kf7 b5
15. f6 b4 16. Kg7 b3 17. f7 b2 18. f8=Q+ { White wins. } *

