{ A. & K. Sarychev, 1930    The a8-knight is under arrest, but the black king hopes to release it, for example, after  1.Kf2?  Kg6  2.Ke3  Kf5  3.Nf2  Ke5  4.Kd3  Kd6  and  5.--  Nc7= }
1. Ne5 Kg7 { ∆  2.--  Kf6  . } 2. Bd8
{ White has built a barrier. The black king can still overcome it, but only at a cost of time and this loss of time turns out to be decisive. }
2... Kf8 3. Kf2 Ke8 4. Ba5 Ke7 5. Ke3 Kd6 6. Kd4 { Zugzwang. } 6... Nc7
{ 6...Ke7  7.Kc5  +- } 7. Bb4# *

