{ Tragicomedies: Ricardi – Valerga, San Martin 1995 } 1... Kg5
{ Apparently logical – the king goes to the queenside. However, in this case restricting the hostile king was much more important.   This could has been achieved by  1...Rh2!  2.Rxb4   2.Ke4  Rh3!  and White cannot take the pawn.  2...Rh3+  3.Ke2  Kg5  @@StartBracket@@only now, when the white king is cut off along the third rank, has the time come to bring the king closer@@EndBracket@@  4.Kd2  Kf5  5.Kc2  Ke5  6.Rc4  Rh8  @@StartBracket@@in order to apply the frontal attack technique@@EndBracket@@ with an easy draw. }
2. Ke4 Rh2 3. Kd5 Kf5 { 3...Rh4  4.Kc5  Kf5  5.Rxb4  is no better. } 4. Rxb4
{ White’s king is comfortably placed in the center and prevents its counterpart from coming closer. }
4... Rh3 { 4...Rh8  5.Rb6  +- } 5. Rb7 Rd3+ 6. Kc4 Rd8 7. b4 Ke6 8. Kc5 Rc8+ 9.
Kb6 { Black resigned. } *

