{ 15/2. B. Breider, 1950  How to fight against the distant passed pawn @@StartBracket@@a4@@EndBracket@@? The knights cannot cross the h3-c8 diagonal, which will be occupied by the black bishop, while the king is placed hopelessly far away. However, it comes to the opposite wing in time, utilizing the Réti idea. }
1. Nf5 Bc8 2. Kg3 Bxf5
{ If  2...d3  , White has  3.Ne6!   Rather than  3.Kf2?  Bxf5  -+ or  3.Ne3?  a3  -+  3...d2   3...Bxe6  4.Nd4!  Bc8  5.Kf2=  and @@StartFEN@@2b5/2P5/4N3/5N2/p7/3p2K1/8/7k b - - 1 3@@EndFEN@@  3...a3  4.Ned4=  4.Ne3  Bxe6  5.Kf2  a3  6.Ke2  a2  7.Nc2=  Another resource is  3.Nd6!  d2  4.Ne4!  forcing  4...d1=N!= }
3. Kf4 Bc8 4. Ne6 Bxe6 { 4...d3  5.Ke3  Bxe6  6.Kxd3= } 5. Ke5 Bc8 6. Kxd4
{ Draw. } *

