{ 15/3. N. Rezvov, V. Chernous, 1991 } 1. Kc7
{ After  1.Ne7?  Bf4+  2.Kb7  Kf6  an attempt to bring the king to h1 fails because of shouldering:  3.Kc6  Ke5!  4.Kc5  Bg5  5.Nd5  h5  with a winning endgame. }
1... Bg5
{ The line  1...Bf4+  2.Kc6  Kg6  3.Kd5  Kf5  4.Nf6!  h6  5.Kd4  Be5+  6.Ke3=  is not dangerous for White. }
2. Kd6 Kg6 { 3.Ke5?  loses now to  3...Kh5!  4.Kf5  Kh4  5.Ke4  Kg4! } 3. Ke6
{ Diagram 16-105 Zugwzang.   White saves himself by chasing two birds at once. If  3...h5  ,  4.Ke5  and his king arrives at h1 safely. }
3... Kh5 { But now he runs in the opposite direction. } 4. Kf7 Kg4 5. Nh6+ Bxh6
6. Kg8 { Draw. } *

