{ @@StartSquare@@Ed. essential information → "Far-advanced passed pawns are pre-conditions for brilliant combinations based on the promotion idea."@@EndSquare@@  D. Gurgenidze, L. Mitrofanov, 1987 }
1. a6 Ra1 { But what should White do now?  2.d7?  Rd1=  is useless. } 2. Bg1+
Rxg1 3. Kh8
{ An amazing quiet move. If  3...Rc1  or  3...Ra1  4.d7  decides.  If @@StartFEN@@7K/8/P2P4/8/8/4k3/8/6r1 b - - 1 3@@EndFEN@@  3...Rb1  or  3...Rd1  then  4.a7  .   And if  3...Rf1  then  4.Kg8! }
