{ R. Réti, 1928    White has a material advantage but his king is badly placed.  1.g6?  is wrong in view of  1...Be5  . After @@StartFEN@@4kr2/5p1K/3p1Q2/1p4P1/4P3/1PP5/7b/8 w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.Kg7?  Be5  White is in zugzwang:  2.c4?  Bxf6+!  3.gxf6  b4  ⨀ -+ If  2.b4  then  2...Bh2  or  2...Bg3  . The same position would be reached, but with Black on move, so White adopts a triangulating maneuver with his king. }
