{ Tragicomedies: Šahovic – Liberzon, Lone Pine 1979  @@StartSquare@@Ed. In Diagram 15-44 EXTRA we will see the solution to White's problems. First, we look at the remainder of the game:@@EndSquare@@ }
1. Ra7 Re4
{ Neither opponent sees the correspondence between the a5- and e4-squares. After  1...Re7!  2.Ra5  Re4!  , White is in zugzwang:  3.Rb5  h4  4.Kd3  Ra4  5.gxh4  Rxf4  6.h5  g5  -+, or @@StartFEN@@8/5p2/5kp1/R6p/4rP2/6P1/3K4/8 w - - 4 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Ra7  h4  4.Kd3  Rb4  5.Kc3  Rb1  6.gxh4  Rf1  7.Ra4  Kf5  -+ }
2. Ra5 h4 3. Kd3 Rb4 4. gxh4 { 4.Kc3!  Rb1  5.gxh4= } 4... Rxf4 5. h5 g5 6.
Ra6+ Kg7 7. h6+ Kh7 8. Ke3 f6 { White resigned. } *

