{ 15/13. O. Duras, 1906 } 1. Ba3 { 2.Bc5 is threatened. } 1... Kc4 2. Be7 f3 3.
Bd8 Bxh2 { 3...f2  4.Bxc7  f1=Q  5.b8=Q  +- } 4. Bb6
{ The bishop has successfully stopped the f-pawn, but Black has also succeeded in stopping White's pawns. }
4... Kb5 { 4...g4  5.a6  Kb5  leads to a transposition of moves. } 5. a6 g4 6.
Bf2 Bc7 { Diagram 16-111 } 7. b8=Q+ Bxb8+ 8. Kb7 Ka5
{ The black bishop cannot be moved. To put Black in zugzwang, White needs to deprive the black king of the a5-square. }
9. Bh4 { Or  9.Bg3  . } 9... Kb5 10. Be1 g3 11. Bxg3 Bxg3
{ 11...Ka5  12.Bh4  Kb5  13.Be1  ⨀ } 12. a7 f2 13. a8=Q f1=Q 14. Qa6+
{ And the black queen is lost. } *

