{ 15/15. J. Hašek, 1937  How to defend the position against the threat of the rook invasion along the h-file? }
1. Kb1 { 1.Re6?  Rh8  2.Rxe5  Kg6  is hopeless. } 1... Kg7
{ If Black plays  1...Rh8  then  2.Rf8!!  Rxf8  3.Kc1  leads to the same drawn position. }
2. Rh6 Kxh6 3. Kc1 Kg5 4. Kd1 Rh8 5. Ke2 Rh2 6. Kf1 Rh1+
{ 6...Rxg2  7.Kxg2  Kh4  8.Kg1  Kh3  9.Kh1  g2+  10.Kg1= } 7. Ke2
{ And the rook cannot remain on the first rank in view of stalemate. } *

