{ 15/17. Kozlov-Nevmerzhitsky, USSR 1964 } 1. a4
{ A pawn breakthrough does not work:  1.h4?  Kc7  2.g5  hxg5  3.hxg5  Kd6  4.f6  gxf6  5.g6  Ke7  -+ Or  3.f6  gxf6  4.h5  g4  and the white king will be mated.   1.Kb1?  Kc7  2.Kc2  Kd6  3.Kd3  Ke5  is quite bad.  And if @@StartFEN@@1k6/6p1/2p4p/p1p2P2/2Pp2P1/8/PP5P/K7 w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.a3?  Kc7  2.b4  then  2...cxb4  3.axb4  d3!  4.Kb2  a4!  5.h4  d2  6.Kc2  a3  -+ }
1... Kc7 2. b4 cxb4 { 2...axb4?  even loses. } 3. c5 Kd7 4. h4 Ke7 5. g5 hxg5
6. hxg5
{ The pawn barrier is built; the b- and d-pawns cannot promote without support from the king. }
