{ Y.Bazlov, 1997  (corrected 2019)     1.Bxa6?  enables Black to gain the piece back:  1...Rh5+  and 2...Ra5. Of course, White may try to do without capturing on a6 and proceed with three pieces against two. These positions have not been analyzed seriously, but some @@StartBracket@@though not many@@EndBracket@@ practical examples confirm that winning chances exist. However White has a more forceful method at his disposal. }
1. Rf1+ Ke7 2. Bxa6 d6+ { 2...Rh5+?  3.Rf5  +- } 3. Kd4 g3+ 4. Kc3 Ra4 5. Nc2
