{ 15/41. V. & M. Platov, 1905 } 1. Ne6+ Ke8 2. Rb8+ Ke7
{ In case of  2...Kd7?  3.Rf8!  (with the threat 4.Ng5)  , White obtains his coveted position immediately, while now he cannot play @@StartFEN@@1R6/4k2p/p2pN3/3P4/7p/5P1q/P4P2/6K1 w - - 4 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Rf8?  in view of  3...Qxe6!  -+ }
