4. Rf7
{ The rook is untouchable in view of the knight fork. White deprives the black queen of the f5-square and creates a threat: @@StartFEN@@4k3/5R1p/p2pN3/3P4/7p/5P1q/P4P2/6K1 w - - 7 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Rf8+  Ke7  6.Ng5  +-. }
4... h6 5. Rf8+
{ After  5.Rf4?  Ke7!  6.a3  a5  7.a4  Ke8!  8.Rf8+  Kd7!  ⨀ White cannot make any progress because he has already spent his reserve tempo on the queenside. }
